reviews.text:
Beautiful hotel, we stayed for a few nights before our wedding (even though we are San Francisco locals) and it was a beautiful experience. The staff were so nice and thoughtful, the suite was large and spacious, an extremely comfortable bed and a dink g area big enough it have the family around for a meals to celebrate together. The staff are very attentive and the hotel feels very secure. 

The Redwood Room was great to gather friends and have drinks, stylish and has a great vibe. 

Overall we can’t recommend this place enough!

The staff was super nice and the hotel is pretty cool. They have a room called The Velvet room or something like that that was a lot of fun. The room itself was just okay. The bed was comfortable but the shower tub situation sucks it's totally old school and for a place of this caliber you would expect to have had a remodel. There are no lights in the closet so it's hard to see your clothes. Not a lot of outlets to plug your stuff in. It's just didn't feel like they were that interested in making sure we were comfortable from a room standpoint once again the staff was amazing and they were all super nice and tell you about the hotel itself

This used to be a hotel where they were more concerned about how comfortable the guests were and how much of a good time to guess we're having. Boasting one of the most colorful bars in the city of San Francisco.... But I'm afraid that they do care and I had become nosy and getting into people's business. I feel that they are so concerned about what their guests are doing they should definitely revamp or shut down the bar if you know what I mean. Only stay here if it's under $250 a night and don't bring your mistress she's not welcome anymore. My

Absolutely amazing! I loved the entire atmosphere! The hotel looks to be built on the 1960s based on the exterior and room design, however, the lobby and rooms are decorated in an eccentric yet classy style. The rewood room is incredibly gorgeous and a great lounge. The staff were extremely courteous and helped with all my needs. 10/10 would stay again!

Awesome classic hotel. The redwood room bar is rad. Stayed in a deluxe suite. Was very large and spacious. Great views of city skyline at night. Rooms are due for an update, especially the bathrooms. Overall had really great time and would definitely stay again.

reviews.text: It is very clean and efficient with great price. Location is very close to attractions and shopping places. Very close to cable cars. Good security. Great for bussiness trips or family vacations.

The location is nice if you like a mix of drunk, loud and homeless people. Pony up another $60 for valet parking and a $30 resort fee. The room is so small I can almost stretch to touch the other wall. The toilet is the perfect size for a toddler. The bathroom door sticks like hell and the knob just came off. Also, my sheet was ripped. To top it off, my mom just gashed her leg on the bed because the damn room is so tight and the bed sticks out to much... NEVER AGAIN!!!
Very nice staff. The hotel was clean but very small. Great location though.
It was in the perfect location! In between Union Square and Market street. A smaller hotel but a very personal experience. The staff there are amazing as well.
The electrics in the room are really flaky (some sockets don't work, some intermittently). Cleaning staff are rude and pushy. Otherwise fine. Good location.

reviews.text:
Very nice hotel in the heart of San Francisco close to union Square. Does not have parking but there is a parking lot opposite to the hotel which is convenient. Has a classic and vintage lift which is a but noisy but adds to the atmosphere. Staff was very cooperative and helpful.

Breakfast was included and one of the best offered in a hotel of similar stature.

Thai staff handling breakfast is unaware of the concept of customer service and needs training. Hence one star less.

I absolutely adore this hotel. They go all in for the holiday spirit. We had the best company holiday dinner.  They were the perfect hosts, service was attentive, the food was superb. There is a parking garage directly across the street, so parking which can be challenging in the city was not an issue.  Looking forward to going back.

A beautiful smaller hotel near Union Square. Decorated in a French style with art covering all of the walls of hallways,  the room we stayed in was small but not tiny, so comfortable too. Downstairs is a wonderful restaurant ran by the hotel with a great  pre fix menu. No parking onsite but plenty of options nearby. Would recommend this place to anyone.

A comfortable bed, quiet and clean room, and cute decor. What more could I ask for? 
The hotel is centrally located and it's easy to get around to restaurants and Union Square.
Very nice decoration. Very good location. Calm and peaceful. But the room we stayed was too small.

result.name: Fairmont San Francisco

reviews.text: A group of us went to the Tonga room for drinks and dinner. The place is fantastic if you've never been before. Very cool and original. Food and drinks can be expensive so I recommend going during happy hour. If you're there during the band performing they will add 10 per person to the check as well. Well worth it!

What's not to love.  I felt as though I'd stepped into an old black and white movie.  A romantic Christmas story...
The tree in the lobby was towering with glistening bulbs.  Excited families were gathering around it for their special shot in their best outfits.  The ornate ceilings were twenty plus feet tall.  A ginger bread house made of real gingerbread tiles....All of it was such a memorable experience.  I hope to go back again someday.  I highly recommend!!

I have been to the Fairmont many times and it is a gorgeous Hotel. A bit pricey but you know that walking in the door. I was working today in the area and the let me in that I could use the bathroom. While inside I walked around and checked out the roof garden and the Honey Bee Garden which was very cool. A beautiful place to stay if you have the cash when visiting San Francisco.

This is the epitome of elegant accommodation.  We visited the hotel's dining rooms and walked through the facility.  Conference rooms abound and rooms are divine.  The lobby is gorgeous and huge.  A perfect place to hang out after dinner and watch the beautiful people come and go.  We enjoyed the decor as much as dinner in the dining room.
A lovely hotel across from Union Square. A nice central location for the city. The rooms are well sized and appointed and pretty quiet. Nice breakfast cart in the morning for coffee and pastries.

result.name: Le Méridien San Francisco

reviews.text: Nice hotel. The parking is ridiculously expensive. Park a few blocks away at the St. Mary's garage. It is cheaper and not far. The staff was great. The one gal at the front desk got me a table on new years eve for dinner when nothing was available! There is parking at the meters outside the bldg at night for free. Check times and street signs. Safeway is not far and lots of dinning close by. You can walk to fisherman's wharf if you want and the pier is just blocks away. My room had a balcony overlooking the bay.

This place is fantastic. Great views of the bridge from the room I was in. The beds and bedding was simply exquisite. Free coffee was great too. Friendly staff as well. I stay in fancy hotels as a sport and this one is near the top as far as a room with a bed goes. Stay there and you won't be sorry.

My short stay here was great!

I arrived late in the night after fighting flight delays all evening. I was greeted immediately and the concierge began to review my reservation and carried out his script of information - short, thorough, and simple, which was about as much as I could handle given the timing. 

I was given a double bed room, which was ample for just me. I found the accommodations very comfortable and the ease of finding all the essentials was great. There was a charging port for my electronics right next to my bed, and I was able to easily access and use the iron to get my clothes ready for the morning. 

The bed was firm and easy to fall asleep in. The bed was lined with plenty of blankets, and I was able to modify the temperature in the room to my specifications with ease. 

In the morning, the breakfast was great - full continental! Definitely go for the russet potatoes! I added a bit of Tabasco sauce for a hearty start to the day.

Overall - the ease from checking in and checking out was the best part. I am hoping for more stays in the future!

I am completing this review for Google Rewards. I attended a conference here that was on the B level. Refreshments were provided the entire time (8am-3am) and breakfast and lunch were great. Staff was very professional and courteous.

The location is relatively close to both public transportation as well as a good amount of restaurants and convenient stores if you have forgotten anything. The room was large and exactly as shown and expected. Would recommend this hotel for sure

reviews.text: Delicious meal with great Peruvian flavor.  We arrived just before our reservation and the seated us promptly.  Our server and other staff were on spot and the food was delicious.  Yes it is pricey and can be very busy.

This is one of the best seafood restaurants in the Bay Area, as well as offering a distinctive range of dishes from Peruvian regional cuisine. The location on the waterfront is one of the more scenic in the city, and though large it's a comfortable place for a special meal. The wine list is extensive and excellent. The staff are consummate professionals.

Three stars for the nice outdoor seating and relaxing tropical decor. Great service from hosts and staff. Unfortunately, only two stars for the food - underwhelming and disappointing from all the great reviews. Good presentation but sloppy delivery - especially the wet water ribbon stains still on the inside of the bowl from wiping it “clean” before serving.
Awesome ceviches! Perfect for a night out with friends. It also has a great view and heated terrace which makes it perfect for dinner.
Excellent Peruvian restaurant specialized for seafood. Next to Bay so location is good, if you want to find place to eat in downtown. Relaxed atmosphere, but not too casual.

reviews.text: One of my area favorites! I’d want to not recommend it so highly so I can actually find a seat next time I’m there. Staff has always been very nice to me, the cocktails and wines are high quality, and of-course the live music and vibe are the main attraction. Oh wait! -best Brussels sprouts ever, worth mentioning believe me

Great Mexican food, 2nd time here & so glad we came back.  Hubby & I split the vegetarian pozole .... yummy Also had no pales enchiladas with cream corn sauce, WOW! Will definitely be back next time in San Francisco.  Good service too.

Two of us ordered a different drink each after waiting a very long time for service (and the place wasn't busy). Drinks were not prepared properly: my simple martini had ingredients from my friend's drink in it. Again, place wasn't busy.
Nice old bar to get a drink while walking around the North Beach area. The make good craft cocktails.

Came by here for dinner and drinks with work colleagues. The venue is very cool and old school. They had a band on the balcony adding to the ambiance. The drinks were a solid 5 out of 5. Really well done. The food was good, tried the burger which was solid too. The service was hit or miss, but wasn't a huge issue.

reviews.text: Came here for a team lunch. Caters to all tastes. The appetizer with Peppers was really good. I had the Crab Sandwich and I loved it. Can book for a large party on Open Table. They have a good drink selection as well. Convenient location near the financial district.
Had a fabulous lunch made up of small plates and wine with a friend.  The food always delivers here. They lost a star for poor acoustics and forgetting a plate.
The food was very good, maybe a bit pricey. Good but expensive wine list. Our waiter was a bit slow though - forgot our wine and didn't seem to really like his job.

went for dinner, big portions.. friends loved the pumpkin gnocchi and salmon entrees. marinated  olives were great. a little too salty for me (i got the orreichette pasta with sausage & broccoli rabe).

We went in for drinks at happy hour (which starts at 3pm) and the bartender wasn't ready. It took about 5 minutes before we could order. The ambiance is fun, not too loud. The drinks were good but not outstanding - good enough to give it another try, so I'm cautiously optimistic.

reviews.text: The black rice and tofu "share" dish is actually a good dinner-size portion for one person and absolutely delicious. I think it's gluten free and vegan, too! Decent scotch options at the bar. The design of the space is a nice mix between warm and  modern / interesting. Servers and bar staff seem genuinely friendly and helpful. Overall a good experience and I want to go back.

Local is a nice, local (South Beach district) restaurant offering salads, pizze, and large plates, with a good wine and spirits selection. Relatively inexpensive for the area, too. The food is always pretty good. The service is good too, but it can be a little slow if the restaurant has a larger party. On my list visit we went a little long between courses, but the staff were proactive in addressing the delay and comped an appetizer, and when it turned out the kitchen was out of something er ordered, they took it off the check and improvised a replacement on the house. The hostess also saw our table wabble a bit, and she had someone come over to address it without our having to ask for it.

All in all, I'd recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for good, uncomplicated food with even better service.
Tasty food and nice chill environment. They have some fancy cocktails in addition to wine. Parking at night isn't too hard since this is more of an office neighborhood.

Great brunch experience with unique food options. I had the slow scramble and my boyfriend had the fried chicken jalapeño sandwich and both were great! Waitstaff was pleasant, prompt, and gave great suggestions. We highly recommend this place!
higher end cuisine, small plates, and pizzas. Nice wine selection, and great ambiance.

reviews.text:
Service was amazing and the food was super. We arrived pretty early in the evening our food came pretty quickly.

Everything was really nice, simple proper food. Decent selection of wines and I appreciate that the entire menu including wine was not pages and pages. 

Prices are pretty good. Even great for San Francisco.

Bland food. Great service. Feel free to skip unless trying to impress a date.
Honestly, everything was beyond bland and needed salt.
Beautiful plate presentation. Beautiful atmosphere. Awesome staff.
Truly a great experience, just not very good food, especially for the price.
Yum! this Italian restaurant still holds its own and mint Plaza. The food seems authentic and is super delicious. And they have a very good bar menu as well.
Amazing food and cocktails. The smelt appetizer was phenomenal and the pats dishes are adequate portions and very high quality. Awesome place for a date or a birthday.

An Italian restaurant nested within a corridor provides a quiet experience.  This place is suited for intimate dining and not so much large parties.  This is also reflected in the menu where there is roughly 20 menu choices to pick from which they have ensured that they do well to produce authentic Italian cuisine.  

The food was great and its handmade efforts were noticeable in their Fettucine and Mushrooms dish. From observing other patrons dishes, the selection is borderline tapas. This may not satisfy customers with a desire for quantity.

For its pricing and quality of food, it is a well-balanced for occasional outings in San Francisco. Food and drink will set you back around $20

reviews.text: Food is delicious, lines are long but service is fast. Omelettes are pretty small, I was still quite hungry afterward. My friend had the French toast, which had vastly larger portions. All of us really enjoyed the food. Staff is friendly and prompt, and the decor inside looks great. Recommended!

Customer service was excellent. Staff assured that customers were satisfied and felt welcome. Nice outdoor seating with fairy lights, as well as seating upstairs. Food was well priced and delicious. Our meal was delivered in a timely manner. Will definitely visit again.

What an amazing find thanks to reviews on TripAdvisor. We were outside before 8am and there was already a queue forming, so we knew we were on to a good thing.

We were right, from customer service to food, to the layout. The whole concept of The Grove is excellent.

It was so good we went two days on the run and that, for us, is unheard of.

Recommended dishes inc. Eggs and avocado, Granola and the French toast.

As described by reviews. Excellent food. Great atmosphere, stylish/posh layout and floor plan. The menu is bright and easy to read. Staff here is polite and well dressed. This was our first visit and we’ll most definitely come back. I can’t imagine there being a better place to enjoy a Sunday brunch.

The last three times I've been in town on business, I've made sure to visit here at least once. It's delicious, dependable, and almost never crowded on a week night. The portions are just right too! I especially recommend the avocado toast, the Denver scramble, and the black tea sangria.

reviews.text: The food was good but not great. The garlic theme was unique. Unfortunately the rolls were cold and our waiter seemed to want to rush us. The sauce and pasta were good but I have had better at establishments where the price point was a bit less. If you want to see the world's longest garlic braid or if you just love garlic, I would recommend giving this place a try.

Like garlic? Garlic any whichaway can be found here. Although I would mention the garlic was not overbearing. Pizza & pasta were enjoyed at our table. Both prepared well. We enjoyed. The Stinking Rose is one of those destination, bucket list experiences that may just be worth a revisit.

One of my favorite restaurants in North Beach. Garlic is in absolutely everything and in vast amounts, so don't go if you don't like garlic. It's cozy and inviting, but always busy, so make reservations. They don't accommodate big parties easily, though it is possible (just a tight fit).

Amazing place. Hole in the wall familia feel, great food. I had the potato soup which was epic, just epic. I wanted a second bowl, and possibly a third. Didn't even need pepper. Melt in your mouth pastry top, creamy garlicky goodness with a touch of potato. I will definitely be coming back soon. Bravo!

Absolutely fantastic. Cheaper than we thought it would be. Great food! See if you can get seated in the outdoor patio, we had a wonderful experience but depends on the people you're sharing it with. The covered booths are nice too if you want a private intimate dinner.

result.name: Benu

reviews.text: The delicacies in the beginning were my favorite - exquisite and delicious. Didn’t like the “main” dishes, eg the chicken leg stuffed with abalone, and really did not like the dessert (winter melon with frozen meringue and a berry sorbet. The service was excellent, striking a perfect balance of being attentive and not hovering. The one weird thing is that they remove the dishes before I finish eating that particular course. This happened twice! I have 3 bites left and they just started clearing the my plates! I thought it was rude and it made me feel rushed.

Asian inspired Michelin star restaurant.  Many flavors were familiar to Korean palette.  Most dishes were inventive and familiar at the same time.  There were a few dishes I didn't love, the faux shark fin, chicken wing stuffed with abalone were a couple.  The 1000 year old egg, hairy prawn (that's what I call it), lobster dumplings, and beef dishes were excellent.  The desserts we're not too sweet, simple and cleansing.  The service was outstanding.  I'm not sure if I'll go back though.

Oh my goodness, Benu is to die for. From the attentive, polite, friendly waitstaff to the perfect wine pairing selections, everything surrounding Cory Lee's food is perfect. But the food itself goes beyond that. I can't even describe it with words. The 1,000 Year Egg was especially amazing, as was the winter melon with chrysanthemum flower dessert.
Impeccable execution by chef Corey Lee and team!  Our New year's Eve dinner was delicious. What a perfect way to end an awesome year and to welcome an exciting new year! Thanks for having us!

One of the top 3 or 4 restaurants in the United States. The food is brilliant, the service is first rate.  Asian inspired haute - cuisine, with a unique emphasis on texture and harmony of flavors. More than a dozen small courses, each a piece of art; with optional alcohol pairings selected by a master that complement and enhance the experience.  I don't think you can find anything else like it in the world, it deserves the accolades it has gathered in the 7 years since it opened.  However, it's an experience, not a dinner, be prepared to spend some time, attention, and of course, money.

reviews.text: We dined in their cellar room. Had to make a reservation months in advance. Very nice space for a group of ten to twelve guests. A few minor interuptions as this is the restaurant's cellar where they retrieve the wines for guests .  All food ordered was delicious and cooked as ordered. The steak was tender and cooked to perfection. Crab salad was very good as well. Everyone in our party was pleased with their food, cocktails and wine.

Boulevard creates the most beautiful and flavorful dishes I've ever tasted. For those who know what TBO refers to, this is the place. Amazing wine list and plenty of non-alcoholic refreshing drinks. Service impeccable. Price...who cares?
Came here for presentation. Very good food. Amazing service. I had sea bass and cheesecake. Probably one of best I’ve had.

Its the perfect place for a special occasion. I brought my parents her for my mom's birthday, and I think dinner took us 3.5 hours with wine, starters, dinner, and coffee with dessert. My parents enjoyed themselves. Whenever we made a comment about the food or service, we were immediately heard. Maybe awkwardly so. My partner teased that the portion was small, which was honest but not expected to be remedied. The waiter then brought an extra portion.
I think this place has earned the good rating they have online. The food is consistently delicious. The service is always on point and the ambiance is just right. I will definitely be returning.

reviews.text:
As a Lover of Thai (though being an American), I was pretty disappointed with this food.   Service was very friendly, quick & the ambiance was nice (hence what you are paying for - SF prices here).  We had 5 different dishes at our table: soup was actually quite good but the rest were mediocre to disappointing.  Poultry & Pork we're noted to "ground" in the meat dishes order - quality of the meat was questionable, being tough & over cooked.  Another dish was found to be bland.  Lastly, we had 2 individuals with G.I. issues after eating - and they usually have iron stomachs.  

Needles to say, I suggest you go elsewhere....find better quality & pay less.
Excellent restaurant. Food is well prepared and served quickly. Definitely will be back.
If You like Thai food this place the ome I recommend. Good food good service.
Great if you're craving traditional Thai! Not an OMG must eat, but pretty solid and authentic without catering to farang palettes

reviews.text: Upscale dining can be impersonal. Not here. We had a large party and we were treated warmly and the service never skipped a beat. Atmosphere was inviting as opposed to stuffy and pretentious. Food was yummy and we were eager to sample each others. The balance of good food, atmosphere and service was very much appreciated.

Awesome place for an upscale dinner in a casual environment. It can get packed but the bar area rotates pretty quickly and they also have a communal table. The Spanish Octopus for dinner was incredible, big meaty tentacles full of flavor and great presentation. For starters, if you love lemons then the lemon chips are a must-try, served with burrata and fresh Italian parsley. Lots of wood and soft lighting contribute to its rustic tavern feel.

Upscale restaurant in SF that you'll definitely want to make a reservation for if you want to go during lunch or dinner to ensure you can get a table. The bar is fun if you can snag a spot, but it's first come first serve. Definitely, try one of their signature drinks. The mixologists do a nice job and their cocktails shouldn't be skipped because you opted for your regular vodka soda or whatever is your usual drink of choice.

Rich selection of bar, nice cocktails. Appetizers were good, too. However we didn't enjoy both portion sizes and overall taste of main dishes. Burger was good, fries too. But both pub steak and wagyu steak was not worth trying. 

Would probably visit for the burgers and drinks, but not the main dishes.
My favorite brunch place in San Francisco. They have the absolute best Challah Bread in the world. The beef short rib is so delicious. And the decor is beautiful. The service is always on point.

reviews.text: I frequent this mall and shop at many of the stores. The shopping experience is unparalleled in terms of upscale specialty stores and architectural design. I find the mall to be pleasantly safe and enjoyable. Many luxury products are available as well as high quality retailers. Unfortunately I must report that I did notice a cockroach in the dining area of the food service section on one occasion recently. But overall, this center is top-quality!

I only stayed here about an hour but the place seemed clean and classy. The spiral escalators were pretty cool. The whole place doesn't try to pack all their spaces with venues and shops so there is a decent amount of breathing room, which I liked.

Huge mall with just about every store you could possibly imagine or want. Very well kept up and clean. Great food court with lots of variety and good quality food. The only downside is that there isn't very good directions as to what floor what store's are on and how to get to them. Overall a nice mall and everything would ever need at a mall!
I love the food court more than the retail stores.  It is not a place to look for good bargain. They do have good selections

This place is HUGE. With 9 stories, it has everything you could ever ask for, and it's in the middle of San Francisco, so you can enjoy yourself in the city, too.

In addition to the great stores--a mixture of high end and general department--there's a huge food court downstairs with some pretty  swanky food court grub. The only downside there is that the food court feeds right into the BART station (super convenient!!!), so we had some panhandlers walking through the tables asking for money. Just part of the SF experience, I suppose.

reviews.text: Tons of beer options!  They had a bunch of their own stuff and like 10 or so guest taps too.  They also had nearly everything bottled, or you could always get a growler too.  I ended up trying 8 or so of their beers, and the standouts for me were the Fresh Roast Brown, and the Chocolate Stout.  The other beers were also good though.  I didn't try any food, but what I saw looked good.  The bartender was great though.  He was a man who liked beer and had no problem giving you his real opinion on the beer options.  He talked us off a couple of beers and in to a few others.  And the recommendations from him that we tried definitely worked out in our favor.

Went out with some friends. We couldn't get into some clubs. Frustrating night, getting late. drove by this place and stopped by. This place change the energy of the party. Great beers, great service, good company. We ended up drunk and laughing about the unfortunate events. Thank you Rogue for saving the night.

Had a great Tuesday afternoon at the bar, with my Canadian friend. We live here. We’ve only had the best service. Female bartender was kind to my dog and super attentive to us. I was so thrilled with her service. While there are other places on broadway this place is absolutely recommended for the pleasant, friendly and welcoming atmosphere. Foods great, beers great, cmon down!

Visiting from Canada, and stopped in during a Tuesday afternoon. For the most part of the afternoon I was the only customer. 

I found the atmosphere snooty and unfriendly. Any and all conversation with female bartender had to be initiated by me. I got the impression staff did not want to engage. Two male staff wouldn't make eye contact, or at least nod or say hello. Totally ignored me like I didn't exist. Not expecting staff to do back flips and hand springs, sit down with me and talk, but at least acknowledge my presence with a hello or something. Female bartender did pay attention to my Emory glass and promptly refilled with my choice. It was just the atmosphere. I would never return. I don't like spending my money in any establishment that makes me feel like I'm not wanted. 

Two stars only because she did pay attention to my empty beer glass. 

For great service and prices visit the brew pubs off Broadway in Oakland like Woods, DivingDog, etc. Great service! That's the reason I left them big tips.
Good selection of craft beers in a laid-back American setting. Nice bar to watch some sports and have a handcrafted beer.

reviews.text: The warehouse turned bar is a chill place to hang out in the Mission, particularly if you're getting off from a climb at Mission Cliffs. There's plenty of space spread across two floors and an outdoor patio. I love how they've placed trees and plants throughout the area. They have a good beer collection. And their for options are quite good as well.

Large beer selection on tap. Bar food is top notch bar food (way above your standard bar menu) but don't expect to have many vegetarian/healthy options to pick from the the menu. Cool ambiance. Hall used to be used by the old railroads in San Francisco. Nice patio outside and welcomes dogs. Insulation is terrible here so it gets cold at night even if you're inside. Also, their door guys are sticklers for IDs so make sure you have one that is current and if you're from overseas bring your Passport. Those country cards won't cut it.

The changing demographics of San Francisco have provided for some interesting changes in enforcement norms. With an ever decreasing amount of couples having children inside the city, there are fewer and fewer teenagers trying to sneak in on a sunny afternoon with their fake IDs trying to get a craft beer.

But what to do? With this traditional demographic of ne'er do wells no longer available, who should be kept out? Who should the friendly security guard at the front eye suspiciously, using the heuristics acquired through years of enforcement to identify as a suspicious character, unable to enter this exclusive establishment without showing her id? 

If you guessed by 82 year old grandmother, well, then you would be exactly right. I mean, I get it, she's got amazing hair. Really, if it wasn't for her stoop, the headscarf common to the "babuskas" of the former Soviet Bloc and the way in which she sniffed disdainfully as she wove her way past the homeless encampment in front of the bar's door, well, you could have mistaken her for no more than 65. A perfect target to not let in because of her lack of ID. 

Totally reasonable. But then methinks so is my 1 star review.

Discriminate against foreigners. Won’t let you in if you don’t have an American ID or bring your passport. As a late 20s person who can prove his age one a driving license + national ID this is absurd. Seriously, who brings his passport with if you are going out for drinks?! That’s the most valuable document you have as an international. Won’t go here again.

Not the most appealing place on the outside, but the inside is awesome and the staff is very friendly! Beer was great. Lots of styles and varieties. The food was rather good as well! I would totally go back!

reviews.text: Our dinner was cooked perfectly and the service was excellent. We told them that we like to eat slowly and have some time between the courses. Of course, we only do this when the restaurant is not (!) jammed. They asked us when they should fire each course and that worked perfectly.

Will was our server and made our dining experience a pleasure. He is attentive, professional, kind, and has a lovely sense of humor. The food was delicious, and we look forward to dining at the Daily Grill in the near future. So nice to be treated with respect and as a valued customer!
I enjoyed a seat by the window to people watch. The chicken piccata was good, not great. The grilled asparagus was tough. I ordered the chocolate bread pudding for dessert--very, very dry.

Came in at 11:00 am, we sat at the bar thinking faster service. We were told the kitchen is switching from breakfast to lunch, had to wait 10 minutes before they could make food. 45 minutes later we received our lunch. There was a bartender switch after our order was placed, and it was a shame, the bartender that came in had no care for his customers, stress on his face with every request. A couple came in and waited 20 minutes to even get a greeting...poor service.

Dinner was great. Came back the next day for Wednesday pork chop special and told by new manager that had to wait an hour for menu to be available. At 3.30pm  At the same time she went ahead with her staff and seated a couple that came after us. When asked why they said oh sorry and too bad for you and everyone else that was waiting to spend money have to wait til 4.30. She said she was new and unable to handle the job.
Wow. Never will go to daily grill again. Spent 300 first night in town. I have never written a review but because it popped up on my phone this is the first and it had to be bad. Daily grill is scratched from my list.

reviews.text: Pleasant cafe inside the Asian Art Museum. It’s a great place to have a light lunch and to enjoy  tea in between visits to different parts of the museum.

Surprisingly good food and value for a museum cafe.  Dim sum basket was 8 pieces for 8.5$.  Lentil soup was great comfort food.  Thai iced tea and blackberry lemonade completed the meal.  Veg noodles and pork dishes available.
Very very rude service!

For museum food, it's more than acceptable! Sure, I'd rather eat in one of the cheaper restaurants outside, but sometimes I'm just one big ball of lazy. If I'm already in the museum, I won't venture out. Lunchtime seems to be the peak when all the tables inside appear full, and the line is long and bustling. Surprisingly, by the time you get through the line, there are tables ready. On a sunny day, there's outdoor seating that one should also take advantage of. 

The food can be a little on the luke warm side because everything is prepared already. They just throw it together when you place the order. It saves them time, and you don't have to wait too long for your food. Everything is served in the most adorable dishes. Condiments available include Thai chili sauce and Sriracha! YUM!
Nice cafe in the museum

 When I last visited I was one of five people there and was ignored by the person who was working front of house and ended up being served by someone who noticed me standing at the counter from where they were working in the kitchen. The gentleman that served me was great though.

If you have plenty of time and want to watch the world go by (or just listen to the various pitches going on all around you) then you can do a lot worse in San Francisco.

Stopped by this location for quick bite before heading back to Los Angeles. Service was fast, food was of good quality, and the atmosphere gave me a cosy feeling. The chef served up a great breakfast sandwich, one if the best I've had in a while. No complaints!

Friendly staff, promptly prepared and tasty breakfast.  The establishment has been in the same spot for eight years...I would take occasional coffee breaks there while at a  long ago job nearby. Such longevity for cafe speaks volumes.

reviews.text: This place was really cool. It's a bowling alley with a scratch kitchen and craft bar. The Mac and cheese is really good. If you want a good drink done right, hit up the bartender by the name of Sean, he will up you with something that will get you right for the night. This is a very cool spot to hang out with friends on a Friday night in the Mission District.
Their hamburger is really good although a tad pricey. Thick, succulent, tasty. So is the not-too-sweet scone with nuts I had for dessert good for the palate.

I had a very difficult experience than most people. I ordered a medium Mission burger, but the burger was severely undercooked-almost raw. When I told my waiter, Mitch, about my burger he said, "what do you want me to do about it?" I asked for a different meal- the fried chicken appetizer. The chicken was also undercooked, but I chose not to say anything. Once I got my check, I saw the server literally watching me sign it from afar. That was the first time I never left a tip. I understand that the food was not his fault, but his attitude and lack of apology was what did it. I was really disappointed as I had been anticipating going to this place for months. Hopefully you will have a better experience.
It's okay. Better than any other bowling alley in terms of cleanliness I think. Staff is friendly and attentive. I will need to return to see for a second opinion.
Popping....😎😎😎😎. So much fun. Food is decent. Staff is great. Especially Dwayne he the shoe guy also plays the jams...Great location.Spacious, airy.  Patio wonderful.

reviews.text: My husband and I came here to try the impossible burger (which by the way is incredible, it really tastes and feels like real meet). We knew this was somewhat an upscale and expensive restaurant and we were fine with it. The food, service and atmosphere are actually really good. The problem was the bill. We had two martinis before the meal. I had a 209 gin and my husband had a Monkey 47. Now, we know Monkey 47 is more expensive than regular find, but they charged us $43 for a martini. That's what I pay for the entire bottle of Monkey 47 at our local boutique spirit store for a whole bottle. $43 for a martini is obscene and honestly  unacceptable. So, overall this place serves good food, the place is great, but we will never get back and would definitely not recommend.

Friendly staff. Good prices for amazing food.   I had the Charleston Golden Rice - yes as a main dish - and honestly, I didn't know rice could be that good. It was buttery and earthy without being too heavy (is that possible?). My wife had the Wagyu A5 beef - a splurge at $90 for 3 ounces - but oh my god, it was amazing. Along with the apps, salad and soup it was an amazing meal.

I came here for the Impossible Burger when it first came out, and have been coming back ever since for the atmosphere, impeccable (read: OUTSTANDING) service and delicious food. 

My bf and I are both vegan and were stunned at how welcoming and accommodating everyone was about it. We've been back for birthdays, anniversaries etc and always have a delicious meal (not always the Impossible Burger!), amazing wine, and an all-around great time. 

I recently had my 30th birthday here in the private dining room and it was stunning. The vegan menu was delicious, the wine was perfect, the service was above and beyond. Special thank you to Tommie, the event organizer, for helping create such a wonderful night. 

I would recommend this restaurant over and over again.

twas a pretty fantastic first taste of this low-key, yet, utterly sophisticated eatery.. only had pomme fritters and a Hemingway, but the class service and elegant presentation left nothing to be desired. my lady and I visited after mentally taxing 9 to 5s and reinvigorated ourselves on splendid ambiance and meaningful conversation. highly recommended.

I love this place!! Super nice place to eat with amazing food. Its a bit on the fancier/pricey side, but well worth the price they charge. Everything here is super fresh and delicious. They also have an amazing drink/wine menu. For all the vegans, vegetarians or adventurous meat eaters they also offer the impossible burger here... a non meat burger that tastes like meat. Im a vegetarian, and every time im in the city I have to stop here to get this burger... its to die for. The flavor is super delicious and seriously tastes just like meat. Other than that there menu has plenty of seasonal options that will please your pallet

result.name: One Market Restaurant

reviews.text: Always a solid go-to.  The servers here are true professionals.  They have deep knowledge and passion for the food they serve and have an understated elegance about the service.  The location is so great (near the Ferry Building, countless office towers and steps from BART and Muni Underground.)  The food is always great.  This place doesn't get enough love!

Imagine old rich person food, but 3x more expensive.  Not particularly imaginative or exceptional.  It was "okay", but for the price you want more.  Either artistic reach or just plain teeth sinking satisfaction.   It provided neither. - which is not to say that it was a bad experience, just not able to hold up to the restaurants that are really pushing the bar (Or holding the line for comfort)

Good food, but high prices. Very poor vegetarian selection. Though they were willing to customize any dish. Still, it is nice to occasionally see vegetarian options on a menu. Especially in California. Especially in San Francisco.

One Market has been around for years! This was my first visit and I came with high expectations. The restaurant itself is huge. They have a few banquet rooms, and tons of seating. It’s a classic restaurant in how the kitchen area is set up and with the food they serve. 

Service was ok. But I was let down by the food. It was just slightly better than ok. One dish was oddly flavored and lacked complexity. The scallop entree was on the bland side. And my dessert cheesecake was made using gelatin. Overall I felt each dish could have used a bit more attention to detail and execution. 

I will also preface that I have a culinary degree from the CIA in New York.

Visited One Market, party of four for 5:30 pm Thanksgiving seating. Bustling vibe in pleasing environment. The satisfaction ended there. Disappointing to say the least.
My $85 Turkey dinner served to me cold. Another of our party also received his turkey dinner cold. Solution was to quickly microwave the meals, and not prepare new plates...cheap way out. I could microwave my own turkey dinner at home. A third member of our party ordered the $85 scallop dish...and received three, yes THREE small scallops. Laughable. A requested diet coke never reached our table, and water service left our party of four thirsty.
We know Thanksgiving is busy, but if you are charging  $85 a plate, along with another $20-30 in taxes and surcharges, you'd better get it right. Very disappointing mediocre meal. Definitely not worth the price. Go elsewhere

reviews.text: Very good and reasonably priced food and excellent service. If you spend >~8.5$ for breakfast you get free coffee and fruits.
Best salad downtown, lots of awesome choices for toppings (my favorite is when they have caramelized pears).  I'm a pretty big guy and I can hardly finish the large salad. Great and friendly service.

My favorite and freshest salad spot in the financial district. Beware, long lines if you go during the lunch rush. Actually the salad bar always has a line but it moves fast! These workers are awesome and so attentive. I always order my own salad with includes spinach/arugula salad mix, topped with marinated tofu, beets and red peppers or edamame. Sometimes I add in their lemon chicken with light balsamic dressing. Their spicy chicken is also to die for and I occasionally order their mac n cheese from the hot food area. Great lunch spot on the go with fresh, tasty ingredients!
Really good for a sandwich or daily specials. The lines at lunch tend to be long. Try to come at off peak times. The salads are awesome because you can basically make your own and they are huge.
If this place had seating it would be 5 stars. This place has such high quality food at great prices.

reviews.text: Good food and good views! Came here with a big group for lunch. But if you're alone or a small group, you can snag a table by the windows with views of the waterfront. Good place to chill after work or relax after a day of touring SF
Excellent food display at our recent company event. Wine selection was solid. Staff went above and beyond to ensure everyone at the party was happy. Would recommend this place to others!
Did not know it was even there !!  We shared 4 appetizers and it was excellent. Service was also very good

We chose Sens for my wife's anniversary birthday celebration because of the spectacular view (you can see SF Ferry Building, Embarcadero Street, and outside ice skating ring this time of the year) and delicious food. I have been at this restaurant before, but mostly for lunch or drinks and my experience usually has been positive. However,  this time with a large group of my relatives (20 people) some of the guests complained of negative attitude their received from the restaurant's staff. In my view Sens is considered an upscale restaurant and I would expect their service to be  impeccable. I will be taking my business elsewhere next time.

reviews.text: A San Francisco staple. The Zuni chicken alone, even with all of its 60min prep time, is worth the trip. Situated directly against Market street, you’ll find Zuni Cafe to be a breath of fresh air surrounded by an “up and coming” area. It’ll take several more years for the neighborhood to catch up but don’t fret, Zuni will be there leading the way. Request a window seat near the kitchen for the people watching, but their upstairs is equally as charming.

A San Francisco classic, but still oh so vital. Arrive early to start your meal with a creative cocktail from the copper bar. Make sure to order extra bread. If you haven't ordered the chicken before, OMG order the chicken! And make sure to save room for dessert. A classy, San Francisco joy of a dining experience. ❤️

Completely overrated and  over priced. It is a beautiful and quaint place . We were not too hungry and did not want to wait an hour to order the chicken. We ordered a pizza which was under cooked and soggy in the center. Surprisingly thin crust, but was so sad and soggy.   The Quang's lamb sausage was better but not worth $20.  We finished with dessert and a coffee that was just okay. I was expecting more flavor from a house made ice cream.  More like an ice milk, no buttery mouth feel. The "compote" reminded me of cranberry sauce from a can.  Our server only checked on us to see if we wanted dessert. Not once after the entrees . Our dishes had been cleared before he came back.  Perhaps we didn't order enough for him.. Save your $.

1. Make a dinner reservation in advance. 
2. Order the chicken for two immediately (it takes about an hour to cook).
3. Enjoy some small plates and drinks, but leave room for the chicken.
4. If you've got room, order dessert.

Romantic atmosphere, seems to attract semi-final clientele.

We went for the burger since many rave it is one of the best in SF. It was delicious & perfectly medium rare as requested, but I don’t see myself going back anytime soon for a 23$ burger with so many other good value crave worthy choices around. Lovely atmosphere and friendly staff. Quick service around 1pm on a weekday.

reviews.text: It was a very good dinner. We we're the last to be seated on a Sunday night so people we're ready to get out but staff was nice. I would recommend everything but the meatballs. Although they were good they were too sweet for me. Sit at the bar around the kitchen if you can. Very fun to watch the cooks.

Food is excellent. Had three tapas and a paella which was plenty for a dinner for two. In fact we didn’t finish the paella. Service was great by the wait staff who do a nice job making recommendations. Definitely get a gin based drink here as they are excellent. Their claaaic gin drink is worth it and extremely tasty.

Amazing staff, fantastic drinks and mouth watering food. Our waiter, Alex, took control of us indecisive ladies and made for a wonderful experience. Everything he suggested was spot on. Such a fun place to kick off our girls trip.

Excellent food! They offer a nice selection of tapas, from skewers to cheeses, so you can try a couple of different items without getting full fast. They also serve paella and other main courses. Prices are mid-range.

We reserved in advance but still waited quite a bit for a table. Service was okay. Our wait staff was pleasant and gave some good recommendations. I like that they don’t bring all the plates at once but we did run out of food at one point and had to wait 10 minutes for the next plate. The dining area is quite busy and noise was intolerable at times.

We had a wonderful experience at this delightful restaurant last Friday evening.  It's a small place with seating for only 72 in the dining area.  Our dinner reservation was for 5:00 pm, which allowed us to have a quiet start to our meal before the room filled up. Our table of 4 enjoyed a few appetizers, drinks and an order of paella.  The paella was delicious,  but there was very little food in the pan for $45. Our server was friendly, helpful and attentive.   I would certainly recommend this restaurant for an enjoyable evening out.

reviews.text: An absolutely fantastic Greek dining experience. A full bar to start, and wonderful bread. If you can, have the lamb that is roasting on the spit in the center of the front dining room. Delicious. Even better is to be seated at the table in front of the open fire. The fish is magnificent. Make sure to save room for the sundae - decadent.

The staff was warm, friendly and informative. They were able to help us choose apps or salads that would feed just the right amount of people. The food was fabulous. The service was excellent and the ambiance in the room was just perfect. The lighting was not to bright, lots of candles to give it a warm, cozy feeling. Kokarri never lets us down, and is always more than a pleasure to go!!
Really good restaurant. Kokkari prepares what are possibly the best lamb chops in the world. The waitstaff and bartenders are beyond the highest standards and set the tone for a wonderful experience.

Everyone talks about the lamb here and I love lamb so I knew I had to try the lamb! I got that to share among 3 of us and they were nice enough to split it up into 3 plates since we said we were sharing (for an extra charge they didn’t tell us about, of course). I thought it was pretty good. It was cooked pretty well, and the lemon wedge was really good with it, but I thought it could have used more seasoning or sauce of some sort. My mom makes rosemary lamb chops at home and I thought they were better. Don’t get me wrong, it was still good, but I would have rather had my mom make them because my mom is that good 😊. The potatoes that came with it were delicious! We also go the pork belly app which was good. It had peaches on top which added a nice sweetness and I really enjoyed it. We also go the watermelon with feta on top. The watermelon was perfect in texture and in sweetness. The feta added a nice saltiness contrast to it. Since we had room for dessert, we got 2 of them to share. I loved the baklava. It had the perfect combination of flaky, sweet, nutty and sweet. We also got the birds nest dessert (not on menu) and it was pretty good except I wish it had been sweeter.

Overall, it was a good meal with nice ambiance. The presentation of the dishes are beautifully plated as well. I personally wouldn’t come back for the lamb since I like my mom’s, but I would recommend it if you don’t have a mom who can cook really good lamb.

Classic fine dining ambience with rustic touches and very friendly staff. We arrived early and we're able to get 2 spots at the full bar before dinner. People were waiting for bar spots, however, shortly after us. Food was DELICIOUS.

reviews.text: The location has the ambiance of a 1970's steak house, very dark with an almost old bank feel to it. We ordered our full meal (salad, soup and mains) with the special request to get salad first and then waited 20 minutes for them to end up bringing the soup and salad at the same time. The side portions while generous their preparation are nothing special. If you're looking for a good steak I would stick with Alexander's.

Butter steak. Eaten everything from dry aged to local farms in Argentina. Butter on quality steak is consistent and reliable. Most other restaurants before your done with first glass of red the steaks cold. Always get another hot plate to keep that meat warm.

Excellent!! The steak was superb!
Jack our server was great! He warned us about the hot plates!! It really did make every bite enjoyable though!! We will be back!

Great atmosphere, cool staff, delicious drinks, and scrumptious steaks!
Highly recommend!  Been here several times, consistently exceeds my expectations.  Always a delightful experience!!!

Wonderful setting and excellent food. The portions are huge so be warned! Wait staff were outstanding - we had limited time as we were on our way to the theatre and they ensured we got our meal in plenty of time so we didn't have to rush.

reviews.text:
The prices aren't cheap, and the portions are small, but the service, food, and cocktails are outstanding!

If you go for dinner, I would recommend giving their Chicken & Waffles a shot. I was expecting something sweet, but was impressed by how savory the meal was. The chicken was perfectly cooked and was well complimented by the homemade Belgium waffle. 

If you're over 21 years of age and enjoy whiskey cocktails, I would suggest trying the Old-Soul Fashioned ... you won't be disappointed.  If you're not a whiskey fan, then I'd recommend the Farmhouse Lemonade.

Farmerbrown is a slow, home-cooking kind of place, with Southern staff and good Southern food. The place is big and spacious, and the food is made with quality ingredients and presented well. Add the homemade, green, spicy sauce if you like spice, maybe add some salt as well. I would come once for the experience if you have lots of time, as service tends to be on the slower side of things. They are known for their fried chicken and shrimp and grits here, so if you're a fan, order those!
Fried chicken with waffles. Who would have thought they work together?  Well they do. Guess I haven't spent much time in the south. Bookmarked - I'm coming back.
The fried catfish was delicious.  The sweet potatoes and green beans weren’t as impressive unfortunately.  But the service and atmosphere were really welcoming, I’d be willing to go back.
One of the best meals I have had in a long time! From the corn bread to the fried chicken and the jambalaya.... all outstanding!

reviews.text: I came all the way from Australia to visit the bar at The Slanted Door, as it was highly recommended, and I was not disappointed! The staff are friendly and professional, and the cocktails are spot on--I should know, being in the industry myself. The food is also sublime. This place does hospitality to a T, and I guarantee you will have a great time if you visit The Slanted Door, regardless of whether you're a local or a tourist. I will definitely be back the next time I'm in town. Thanks again!

My wife and I love this place and we have been there a few times over the last few years, most recently on NY eve last week. The food is absolutely outstanding, though not cheap. The chef melds Asian and American flavors into something pretty unique, and the execution is flawless. The ambience and service have also been consistently excellent. 

I would normally give them a 5-star review but the wine list holds me back, as it is pretty weak both in terms of the selection available and the quality of the wine served. This is less true when you buy a bottle but the selection is still incredibly biased toward German/Austrian wines...I don’t remember seeing so many Rieslings on a wine list at any other restaurant, outside of Germany perhaps. This really needs to be addressed if they want my fifth star.

Let me start by saying the food is great. The service is far less than great, maybe it's because they are so busy, or maybe because they are so busy it's okay to piss off the few. 

We checked our BANK STATEMENT today and it APPEARS our very lackluster waiter first input the wrong total into the credit card machine. He then did it correctly we paid and left. BUT there is still a PENDING CHARGE and the bank has NOT RELEASE THE EMPLOYEES MISTAKE YET. 

I would not be so upset if the employee at the Slanted Door, One Ferry Building was not so RUDE the entire evening. He acted like he was doing us a huge favor by taking our order. 

The only thing I can say is CHECK YOUR BANK STATEMENT!! And make sure your waiter loves what they are doing because this guy was rude and not the sharpest tool in the shed.

The best "modern" Vietnamese I've had. It's expensive, but utterly delicious, with good cocktails as well. This sprawling restaurant is located at the northern corner of the Ferry Building, and for San Fran is extremely spacious. There's also outdoor seating and a takeout window on the inside hallway.

Between us, we had four shrimp, chicken, and vegetarian dishes (they are served "family style") and all were superlative-- intense flavors, crisp textures, balanced seasoning. The dishes are the appropriate size to share among 1-3 people, depending on appetite.

Two rounds of cocktails were equally tasty including my orange Caipirinha. Service was brisk, polite, and efficient.

It's pricey, especially if you are expecting Vietnamese to be a "cheap" cuisine (Asian cuisines as a whole get that bad rap), but then again this is waterfront in San Fran-- pricing is as expected considering that location.

High end interpretation of Vietnamese dishes.  Extremely popular, so best to get reservations.  Couples can usually squeeze in at the bar.

Avoid the extended dining area near the back end of the bar.  It was an afterthought to increase seating, but has no ambience and you're basically left staring at walls.

The main dining area has gorgeous views of the Bay Bridge.  Food is delicious, but has been so over hyped, better to tamp down expectations and you'll walk away very pleased.  Service is great.

We regularly eat lunch before the theater. Service is gracious, city street view always interesting. We get favorites like Cilantro Shrimp salad and excellent soup. Quality of the food is consistent, spices enjoyable, there is a full bar for enhancements.
Great Fresh Fig and Berry salad! Also good choice of wine.

Paid $20 for a salad and found a bug added to the mix.  When we told our waiter he offered to replace it with a new salad but it was too late.  They ended up not charging us for the one salad but overall very disappointing experience.

result.name: Marlowe

reviews.text: I don't understand how this place has such a high rating. After looking for places to eat that were open on a Friday night at 10:30pm, found this place on Yelp. What a huge mistake that was. Good luck finding parking. The food is overpriced and mediocre.   For two ny steak dinners and a pork chop dinner I paid $160. That was with three cokes and a $20 five shrimp appetizer. Shrimp tasted like bleach from the pot they were boiled in. The steak was not medium well like i ordered. Chef must only cook rare and well done. The twice baked potatoes are the size of golf balls and the steak was only 8oz max after cooking. I guarantee there are better places in SF that don't cater to trust fund hipsters sipping a glass of $10 wine all night.

Absolutely exquisite cuisine. Mushroom soup was rich and smooth with small pearl onions. Polenta with mushrooms, arugula and poached egg is sumptuous and has a lovely tang. Service is attentive. Great location if you are on your way to the train.

Just coming into the restaurant, you can feel that the foundation is hollow but stable. You can definitely feel people moving. The whole place itself is beautiful-wonderful atmosphere for dates as the lights are dim. One of the defects is that it is very crowded. There is room to breathe, but not enough room to move around. Because everyone is crowded into a small area, there are voices bouncing on the walls and it is very loud. Not loud enough to not hear across the table, but speak up when inside. 

For an average meal that costs around twenty to thirty dollars I would’ve expected better, but the food quality was not so great. The meal was either soggy or dry, not to extremes. Definitely salty or bland, there was no in between. 

You do have to reserve a spot in order to grab a table, so just in case, book hours in advance.
Cuisine at lunch is a good variety and high quality. Atmosphere informal but cozy. Clientele is mono culture tech venture types so go for food but not ambience.
Everything was great!  Our selections of burger and fries, prawns, radish and avacado salad absolutely delicious! Highly recommend this lovely little restaurant.

reviews.text: My wife and I had breakfast there. Staff were attentive and courteous.  Breakfast was great. Open floor plan and natural lighting adds for a nice atmosphere.  The big plus was that the music was mostly 70's top 40 and the volume was subdued.

Everything was amazing the service and drinks from Wemerson was great (I don't think you can do better then him) and the food was the best I had in SF as of yet.  Thank you for the good food and amazing service.  From a New Yorker

Poor. The food was decent tasting, but came out cold. The service was awful. We waited forever to find a host to seat us. After placing the order we had to repeat details several times. We couldn’t find anyone to give us our check. Forget about anything besides regular coffee; latte was terrible... not a latte.

Why go here when there are tons of other options around?

This place was almost completely empty when I entered for breakfast, and that made me question my decision to eat there. I had the eggs benedict, and they were delicious though on the high-priced side. I did not like the chairs that they used at the dining tables semicolon not having a back on a stool makes it very uncomfortable.
Good, went there with co-workers for SF Dine About Town. Loved the fried Avocado.

reviews.text: The host was pleasant, he did a good job of noting reservations and greeted people as they walked in. The bone marrow was delicious, the halibut was buttery, tender and fresh. The berry margaritas on the rocks was so tasteful. The only complaint, our server was very rude. I already felt out of place dining at this fancy restaurant but felt even more out of place due to our servers' treatment. She was polite to every other table but not to mine.

Beautiful ambiance – themed like an aquarium. It’s very unique. It almost feels like the swing era with the booths. The dishes were incredible. The presentation was A class and service was impeccable. They had very polished servers who knew the etiquette. I think the price reflected the level of service and food. Overall I felt we received the value for our food. It is typically difficult to get a reservation here but we were lucky to find an opening and they did their best to accommodate us – tourists from Canada and Germany.

The Service at Farallon was outstanding. The waitstaff was more than accommodating.  I had my 2.5yr old son with a small wedding group and I can't say enough how accommodating they were. The food was wonderful.  The atmosphere was great. I would absolutely return and recommend this to others to dine.  I was extremely impressed with the whole waitstaff, was a wonderful experience!

I’m in from out of town and decided to try Farallons out. Was not disappointed. Had great bar service with drinks and appetizers. Till they served food at 5:30pm. We continued to dine at the bar and had a knowledgeable waiter with very solid suggestions. Will definitely come back when I’m in town.

This is probably one of the top ten restaurants in which I have dined in my 60 years. Excellent atmosphere, appetizers, entrees, wine, dessert, and service.

Excellent staff, attentive service. Will definitely be back on my next visit.

reviews.text: They are known for the fried chicken. It was good, but I didn't think it was the best fried chicken I ever had.  Their whipped potatoes was delicious, just way too watery and didn't come with a spoon.  Over all, the food was tasty, but not something I would suggest to a friend since there are so many other places around.  The table service can be improved a little.  The hostess was very nice and kept me posted with the availability of the table even for the short wait we had.

This restaurant was very flexible when our plans all fell apart. We had a really nice dinner of their signature fried chicken  and tavern burger.  The burger was cooked perfectly, but my chicken was a little salty but good. 
And their deviled eggs were really good.  Also, don't forget to keep asking for more of their signature popovers, yum.

Great breaded chicken, hesitate to call it fried chicken as that conjures thoughts of greasy chicken, which is the farthest from the taste of this chicken. Not up for all that chicken as an entree, order the City salad with 2 pieces, great combo. Gotta start with the deviled eggs, delicious.... Fries and home made chips looked decadent, but didn't taste...this time😀

Super yummy fried chicken. The City salad is huge. I ate half of my salad and 1 piece of chicken for lunch and took the rest home for dinner.  The deviled eggs are just ok, need something to give them some kick maybe. Popovers are good but its weird that they give you 1 piece and then walk away. I don't eat a ton of bread but still think its odd. Fries are good. You can get an order of fries even though they aren't on the menu.

Excellent atmosphere, food quality and service. Our server Joe was awesome, gave us fine-dining quality service and the burger was REALLY GOOD. Great selection of cocktails and wine as well. The only reason I give it 4-stars is because we had a weird issue with our card being charged a few times, but they ended up resolving it.

reviews.text: Very limited menu.  The butternut squash soup was very good but that was it.  Onion rings were cold, beef brisket was more of a fatty pot roast drowned in a sour BBQ sauce, served cold, the pizza my wife ordered was tasteless, and likewise cold.  Service was friendly but very, very slow.  Long delay between seating and ordering, and again between the soup/salads and entree arrival.  By the time the dessert menu arrived, we just wanted out of there.  Our daughter mentioned she passed a table as we were leaving where she overheard a couple discussing sending their brownie dessert back. Now it's six hours later and I woke up with acid reflux and a sick feeling.  Bottom line: while highly recommended by friends who live here, they had not been in years.  Wanted to like this far more than we did.  Disappointing.
It's a long time since I have been here and I'm still impressed. Good value for the money. Tasty food and friendly efficient service. No problem finding parking

During lunch hour, we were seated promptly, and our orders were served quickly.  The food was fresh and hot, but the service after that was extremely slow.  The remodeled dining area is nice, but was too loud when packed with the lunch crowd.
Very rude staff especially the manager.  Very unprofessional and full of attitude. Overpriced mediocre food and drinks although the drinks were good.  Would not recommend.
Professional. Courteous. Best drinks I've ever had in this city. No much more to say.

reviews.text:
Very nice cozy place. Good for a dinner with friends or business. It's my third time here. Very nice menu. If I have to make remark not to give them 5 stars is that the wine list can be better and also the beer selection.
Is a little crowded, bit of you have to wait a bit it's worthy the wait

Incredible breakfast, hard to come up with faults. I love cooking breakfast at home but rarely go out to eat for it, we ended up in SF just about the right time and came to Nopa to start the day off right. Coffee was perfect and all 4 of our unique dishes were equally enjoyed. I will say despite the ratings that the burger isn't the best in the bay despite it being good and you should look elsewhere if you want a burger. One crazy thing is that I dropped my napkin accidentally and had a new one handed to me by the time I bent down to pick it up. That's some serious Michelin Star Rated service!

First of all, they have the best burger I had in San Francisco. The best! Just for that they get 5 stars. It's so good and delicious. The other things on the menu are also great choice! We also really enjoyed the brunch. It's a great place!!!

Wow!  The pork chop is unbelievable!  I almost don’t want to tell anyone and keep it a secret. Unfortunately, this place is very difficult to get into. I’ve eaten at the community table and at the bar when I couldn’t score a table. There will still be a wait for those. Everything else I’ve nibbled on from friends plates is great, but I can’t tear myself away from the pork chop.

I will keep it simple and heartfelt. Great tasting food from a limited menu of brunch options. Waitstaff is polite and friendly but the food takes a very long time to be prepared. Prices is reasonable and seating can be difficult with the limited space.

reviews.text: Saturday night and we walked in, got seated in 5 minutes. The hostess was quick to tend to us. We had our Mom in a wheel chair. No problem here! They accommodated us. The food was served in a blink of can eye.  And let me say. We enjoyed it! Every morsel. And desert too... fantastic.

Top of the line crab! My bother and I shared the "lots of crab" for two and it was very very good! Everyone in my group really liked what they ordered.  The service was good, but not great.  The prices seem fair. I would give it 4.3 but Google only allows 4 or 5.

A great place for fresh seafood and small plates. Quite pricy, but worth checking out. The freshness of the ingredients and the high level of technique definitely impressed. Even the food on the kids menu came out with a high attention to detail and a dedication to quality that I don't usually see in children's food at restaurants. I'd definitely give it another go some time.

Our server was super friendly and helpful, in fact the entire staff is that way. Located right on the pier, this place offers one of the best seafood, we had an entire crab seasoned with garlic and it was delicious. We also had their platters with fish which was just ok. Overall, this is a nice place to visit if you're in San Francisco by the pier.

A little pricey but the view is great and the food very good.  No one should be shocked at the price of food here its in tourist trap  and has probably one of the best views around.  The shrimp cocktail was better then I would have expected I would recommend if you like that as an appetizer. If you like unsweet tea then don't get it here it has to come from a tap it has a slightly off taste to it.

reviews.text: Overall, I'm not sure this place is worth a second trip. The food isn't bad by any means, but the restaurant definitely gets crowded and busy, so expect a wait if you go anywhere near lunch time. Additionally for the price, the food just isn't worth it. Feeding just myself with a just middle of the road ramen and water, ended costing just under $15, which granted there is a $.35 card charge on there you should be aware of (oh and the $13 minimum per person and $12 per card (max 2) minimum). Not a bad meal, but not worth its scratch. There are better, less crowded options very near by

Usually there is a long line for lunch. Since we're eating early. We were able to get a table. The ramen was good but I felt that it lacked depth. The price is typical of sf so I wasn't surprised. The service was quick and there was no pressure to leave after we finished. I would recommend this underground ramen.

I personally thought the food was amazing! I love the atmosphere, it's not perfectly like Japan but it's nice and cozy. It tends to get very busy so expect a wait unless you get there at the perfect time.

Overpriced and mediocre.  This place used to be good when it first opened across the street.  But over the years the price hikes have been steep.  This last time, the noodles was not very good-it was no longer chewy and seemed thinner and slightly overcooked.  The noodles for me was the differentiator.  Now that it's no longer is, I don't have a hankering for the noodles here anymore|.
It was alright. I'm not much of a ramen afficionado but nothing about this place was particularly amazing. Beers are expensive ($6/pint). Limited seating means you sit in cramped tables.

reviews.text: I love this place. The food is fantastic for both dinner and breakfast. Although the breakfast menu is quite small. I have not had the pleasure of tasting the brunch menu yet but I looking forward to it! I highly recommend this place for delicious and hearty upscale dinning. The price is a little high compared to everyday food but it is well worth it.

We went to the Cavalier last night for Valentine's Day.  5:30 seating.  I have to say, they treated us like queen and king.  We got a great table and excellent service for the entire evening.  Valentines's Day has a 4 course fixed price service, with wine pairings as an option.  My husband had the steak and I had the duck breast.  The vegetables were wonderful.  The wine pairing was fantastic.   But really, it was the service that made the evening so special.  I can't wait to return and bring friends with us.

This place is amazing.  To my fellow Americans, try the scotched eggs.  You won't be disappointed. Had the burger and it was great (but small).  Others had the steak, fish N chips and ravioli.  Everyone loved their food.

The food was pretty darn good and diverse British offerings, but the service was slow. We were there on a Friday afternoon for lunch. The brussel sprout crisps we're scrumptious and the black currant refresher was a nice non alcoholic delight. The space is beautiful and upscale.

I highly recommend the scones (if you like sweets) and anything with bacon in it. The breakfast sandwich had a little too much bun for my taste but it was delicious and the egg was the perfect amount of runny. The staff was excellent and very attentive.

reviews.text: Service is impeccable. We got our oysters before our drinks and weren’t even mad about it (because we were there for the oysters mainly), but before we knew it our server had sent out a “gift” from the kitchen to make up for it. The flavors were great. Coincidentally our least favorite oysters were the Hog Island namesake. But our favorites were the ones recommended by our server, so I would definitely trust a recommendation here! Also our “gift” was grilled oysters and we never try any cooked oyster - I am so happy he sent these out since I never would have known how delicious. Do yourself a favor and try the garlic and the chipotle grilled oysters.

Fresh fresh sea food and particularly the oysters. Wait times can range from 20 - 45 minutes, but the time goes fast since you can order drinks from the bar. Appetizers ate pricey, and hit-and-miss. Recommend you still to the entrees and oysters.

Great place for food, atmosphere and drinks. Had oysters combo plate, grilled oysters and the grilled cheese sandwich. All were fantastic and the service was good. Nice place to enjoy SF and it's food.

Hog Island has been my bay area home for oysters and fresh seafood for a decade. Having eaten oysters all over the world, I believe the Hog Island oysters are of the absolute highest quality and have the fingerprint of being locally farmed and sourced. One friend remarked that they just taste better because they’ve not been jostled to the same extent as oysters that have been flown, which makes more sense with live animals like fresh oysters. The clam chowder is my favorite because of its brothy consistency. With a cold local IPA, this is one of my favorite meals.

There's no better place to get fresh oysters in the city than this place. They offer fresh raw oyster in the shelves. And also bake ones, or cook other ways in creamy soups and chowders. If you want and oyster Feast, this is your place.

reviews.text: Outstanding. Incredibly high quality service and surroundings, especially in downtown SF. The food is quite good, though some of the dishes are relatively standard fare. I had a lunch special which, at $38, is a bit expensive for SF, but was still worth the price. The drinks are very clever and well mixed (limited authentic Chinese options on that front). But the real point of the restaurant is to provide the high caliber luxury experience that establishments of this variety want to, and Hakkasan absolutely delivers on this front.

Lovely high class dim sum and dinner plates.  Vegetarian dim sum was delicious. Sea bass was incredible. So tender and flavorful. Short ribs also very flavorful. Only wouldn’t recommend the pumpkin duck item. Pumpkin outside was too thick and cakey.

A great spot if you want to grab either a lunch or dinner. Once inside, you feel the warmth from the decor. Apart from that, staff does a wonderful job in communication with both guests and colleagues. Waiting time for the food can be less than 10 minutes which is extremely fast. Along with that comes great, and fresh food. Overall a great restaurant with logical price/quality ratio.

Decent but overpriced food. Great table service but our reservation was seated 45 minutes after our time. Pacing was also really slow. It felt like a place you get expensed when you take someone there for a business dinner, so if that's your vibe, go for it. The food isn't bad. However, if you're there for a date or something, hard pass.

This is a high end Chinese restaurant.  The interior is fancy and nice.  I enjoyed the fancy atmosphere and excellent, friendly waiters' services. The food was very good. There was only one person at the front, and we had to wait for about 10 min. to be seated. although we made a reservation.  I give 4 stars instead of 5 because it was a bit expensive for me.  With wine, it costs us over $150 per person.
