result.name: Waterbar

reviews.text: Wow.... one of the best experiences I've had dining out yet. We must have had for servers plus the management and bartenders waiting on us. Wonderful View at our table and I noticed most tables all have a great view of the Bay Bridge. A little pricey but you got to experience this place at least once we were celebrating our son getting into college what a great time we had four of us plus a bottle of wine and all the trimmings appetizers dessert &  plenty of drinks... I think the bill was around $500...automatic 18% tip fyi, ....I felt it was justified.

If you love seafood, this is the place for you. It's right on the Embarcadero, on the water side, almost under the Bay Bridge so it has absolutely stunning views. The food is so good, I can't even explain it. Highly recommend getting the oysters and both the starter and main course I had were perfection. While it is on the pricey side it's not going to break the bank which is amazing for the quality of food and service you're receiving. I can't wait to go back again, especially when it's a little warmer so I can sit outside on the patio (they have a lot of heaters to fight the cold though too).

Best east coast oysters I’ve eaten so far on the west coast. (I’m partial to that Atlantic brine.) Great non-fussy mignonette (no cilantro, yessss). The cocktail sauce was solid too if you’re into that. Phenomenal views of the bay bridge at night.

Bartender forgot my beer order but felt bad and comped it. Great service, will definitely be back for more oysters!

One of my favorite restaurants in San Francisco. Located at the base of the Oakland Bridge. Fresh seafood fresh oysters as well as some steak options. Good atmosphere on the water with great views day and night also the sister restaurant next door the epic is a great Steakhouse

The view is spectacular.  With that being said,  our expectations of the food was average.  The mussel risotto was amzing.  The texture of the mussels was perfect.  We also indulged in the oysters.  The prix lunch was a great lunch at a great price.

reviews.text: The food is phenomenal! Excellent beer and cocktail assembly as well. If you need food, you need the Boardroom.
Great food, good beer selection and the best customer service at a sports bar in SF by far.
Quality food , good prices and a friendly bartender. Took good care of our group of people
Bacon wrapped tator tots. Quality food, great service and wide selection of beer and booze.

I want to give this place five stars because the food was unbelievably delicious. We went for brunch on a Saturday and service was super fast despite them only having one cook, and us having a large group. However, the place itself is a total dive. It's dark and dingy, they keep kegs in the bathroom, and there was a dog walking around the restaurant. I love dogs, but I thought that was a little strange...

result.name: Brenda's French Soul Food

reviews.text: My eyes may have been bigger than my stomach, but dang that was so good. Had the BFC : 2 delicious pieces of succulent fried chicken with tasty spices in the coating, on top of fries and a biscuit. Also came w some tangy homemade pickles and coleslaw. Good stuff. Well worth the $13 because i couldn't finish the whole thing. Our server seemed odd and almost acted like she didn't like serving us, but the food came fast and it was only at the end when we couldn't see her anywhere when our server changed to someone else magically. She wasn't terrible, but something didn't seem right - maybe it was just an off day for her. In any case, food was great and we were taken care of by staff.

Brenda’s makes up for the VERY long wait (over an hour) with an amazing dining experience. Our food was delicious and came out surprisingly quick. Anything on the menu is great but make sure you order the beignets. The coffee was also fantastic. Great overall experience.

This place is really good, just be prepared to wait. My group of 3 waited over an hour but were lucky enough to grab a seat inside while we waited. Once we got in the service was quick and our food came out very fast. I had the chicken etouffee and it was extremely good.

Awesome place with great food.  I went around 10am and there was only a 5 minute wait because the hostess was accommodating a takeout order.  But the best part (beside the food) was I made it out in about 20 minutes and I had leftovers!!  My waiter was great.  One of the highlight of my Bay Area trip!!

Go here for soul food! The fried chicken is amazing. Came here after a wedding down the street at city hall with a small group of 5. The staff was even nice enough to convince the kitchen to make the chicken before the usual hour (~11 am) for the celebration.

result.formatted_address: 661 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
result.name: ThirstyBear Brewing Company

reviews.text: My wife and I flew in on a Thursday night at 9:30 from Indiana.   Closing time was 10pm.  Server was very nice but immediately came to our table and told us it was last call for drinks and food then hovered over us.  We didn't understand the menu items as we have never had this type of food before so we ordered the burger to be safe.  It was very good and enjoyed it a bunch.  Lucky choice.  The server came back and was very nice the entire time.  My problem is if you have a closing time then you need to have it be the closing time.  OR.... set the closing time earlier so we have time to eat and enjoy the place after walking 2 miles to get there.  Maybe it's different in the Midwest but if you close at a set time then you treat every customer the same and have "last call" at the closing time and not 1/2 before.  We visit breweries for the atmosphere first then the beer/food second.

Not a good place for large groups.  Food late and overcoked.  Waitress was wonderful; manager was not pleasant.  On the way out, was almost pushed over by another server carying food to his table.  Overall I would be more satisfied with street hot dogs than this place!

Attended an SF Travel event. Had not been here in a while, delighted to see food quality and presentation still excellent.  Busy evening in the main floor with diners.  I will go back as it is close to my work.
Terrible service. Asked for a medium burger, got a well done one. Could not get them to change it. Manager was a jerk.
Very nice local brewery doing organic beers. Friendly staff and nice atmosphere.

result.formatted_address: 199 Gough St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Rich Table

reviews.text: It's no wonder this restaurant is one of only four in San Francisco that received their first Michelin Star in 2017. Rich Table serves up an ever changing menu of gastronomical delights that will awaken your taste buds and your imagination. It is almost impossible to get a reservation at this restaurant right now, due to their increased attention from their new status as a Michelin Star restaurant, but if you are willing to go at any time, the food is definitely worth the wait. The Chef's Picks included several rounds of appetizers, an intermezzo, a main course and dessert. Each round was as different and delectable as the one before and everything on the menu a work of art. If you are looking to impress a date, or a boss, this is the place to take them!

My expectations were high for Rich Table. We chose the tasting menu and it started well with a selection of delicious and original flavors. However I don't feel the fried sole worked particularly well with, what was an excellent cut off fish, obscured by batter and tartar sauce. The pasta was a fairly standard mix of flavors and the desert was a dark chocolate and mint combination which reminded me of something you could buy in a supermarket. Waiting staff were fine but certainly below what I would expect to earn a star. All in all it was enjoyable but for the price I expected a bit more.
Complex menu (which can be good but not in this case) and pretentious air... and staff felt unapproachable. Space was small and could have been a nice intimate experience.

Can’t believe I’m only now discovering this place. From start to finish everything about this restaurant is amazing.  Ambiance is on point and the food is to die for.  The richness of flavor, every item was a 10.
The chef's tasting menu was amazing. Great service and even better food.

result.name: The Grove - Hayes Valley

reviews.text: Very congenial atmosphere here.  We got friendly with people at the tables on both sides of us.  I gave the homemade pastrami a try.  It was good, but it is served on sour dough; I'll take mine on rye with Russian dressing at the Jewish deli.  The locally made chocolate cake was excellent.

Great spot to grab breakfast! We wandered around for an hour trying to find a breakfast spot without a huge line and decided to try The Grove. Yes, there was still a line, but it moved quickly because you order at the counter. The New Yorker breakfast sandwich was fantastic and I even tried the French toast, which was killer as well. I would highly recommend The Grove and will definitely be back when we get back to SF.

This charming location situated in Hayes Valley is a perfect place for breakfast,lunch and dinner. With a great outdoor seating area, a great menu and excellent service this is a spot you will find yourself coming back to time and time again. The prices are very reasonable which is hard to find in the area. Most of all I always suggest their lavender lemonade!
Great place to eat alone...or witb others. Umlimited coffee refills, have a drink and snacks with friends, eat a tasty meal before a concert.  I obviously enjoy this place, hope you do too!

In the 5 days I was in San Francisco we ate there 4 times. Pot pie is wonderful and there is this salad with tortilla chips and a lime dressing that will make you want to lick the bowl. I had it the first day and the second time my group went there is because everyone wanted to try my salad!

result.name: Flour + Water

reviews.text: We walked in on a Sunday night, half expecting an hour wait, but were pleasantly surprised when we were seated within a half hour at the bar. The trout appetizer was light, refreshing, balanced, and savory. The freshness of the satsumas paired nicely with the savory quality of the dressing and delicate flavor of the trout. Our pastas were excellently composed as well, with special attention to textures.

Was a little hard to coordinate with the front desk for a seat.

But the food was delicious, the service after that was amazing and we were not rushed at all.

Waiter was really descriptive with the foods and helped us make great selections.

We were pleased to show up and sit at the communal table after 20 minutes. The food was spectacular. My boyfriend and I didn’t care for one of the appetizers, because it wasn’t quite our taste. We didn’t eat very much of it. Our waiter came over to check on us and inquired about the uneaten appetizer. He took it off of our bill without saying anything to us. Great service and great food.

A special dining experience with a fresh and delicious "farm to table" feel, though not cheap but great for a special experience. Also hard to get into.

Tip - To get there as a walk in for dinner you have to get there at least 30 minutes before they open. (At leas this is how I got in.)
Delicious, creative noodles. Perfectly composed salad. Fantastic wine list. Amazing chocolate pudding. Yes please, give me more

reviews.text: I like this place, food was very good and our server was attentive all the time. People were starting to have fun, and I like that. Will come back again.

Great brunch/hangout spot on Union. Bartenders are on point and they even do a bloody Mary bar! Food is good, I usually do a benedict. Sit outside and watch the pretty people and great doggo's go shopping. Can't really go wrong here.
Food was very good. Service was slow. They ran out of Bloody Mary mix on a big brunch day. One of the best spinach and artichoke dips I’ve ever had.
Love this place! Great food, great drinks, great everything! Good looking crowd and a good time!
Fun place to have pub food and drinks. The large open space can be noisy but you can still hear the conversation in a big group.

reviews.text: This place had great reviews so we thought we would try it.  I can only speak to the three items we had:  Burgers, Fries, and Brussel Sprouts.  The fries were excellent, nice and crunchy.  Unfortunately the burgers (3 of them) were all overcooked.  Well-done at a minimum, very dry.  Since all 3 burgers were the same, must assume this is how they do it.  Avoid the $18 burger.  Unfortunately, the Brussels were equally as bad but for a different reason.  A citric flavoring was added.  You could tell it would have been good, but it was over-applied and everyone at the table felt it was too sour.  We could not finish it.  Bottom line, could be entirely what we ordered but what we got was no where near worth the price.  My sons would not even finish their burger.

Food was amazing and great pairing of flavours and ingredients used. Upscale breakfast spot. So for the price you pay you would expect the stuff to least land out steak nice to cut into your meal... but we had to request for it... and she was also in a rush to send us off. The moment we finished our meal, she billed us out. Such a shame that the restaurent would have this kinda behaviour. But the lady who received and sat us down was very sweet and pleasant:)

Great food and friendly service. Definitely recommend the Chicken sandwich (only available on Tuesdays). Truffle fries was an excellent addition! The fries were perfectly cooked with the absolute best crunch! We started with some meats and cheeses, had a delicious cocktail w/elder flower, and finished with our main dish. Great please to sit at the bar, be social, and have great food.  Forgot to take pics!!!
Nice place as a bar, good service but bad food and kitchen

This is a great place to spend time with friends. You'll have plenty of time  to catch up before the food arrives, and when it does, it's so unremarkable that you'll really get to focus your attention on your companions.

reviews.text: Love love this place! Delicious food, great service and staff, and super cool ambient and cozy setting. We had the trout and swordfish and they were both incredible (especially the trout!). Chocolate cake dessert was amazing as well, very rich. Live music was a lovely touch too. Will definitely be back!

I stopped by here for a quick meeting and drinks during the JP Morgan conference. It was a very wet and rainy day, and this being set up in an alley, definitely made this feel a lot like friends.

 Unfortunately it was a little bit cold, and they weren't letting anyone sit inside who did not already have reservations. Still a nice atmosphere, and maybe I'll be back there to try the food as well.

One of my favorite places in Union Sq area to get good wine, excellent light meal, and espresso drink, with the atmosphere to match. It is located in one of those famous SF alleyways, Claude Lane. Live music several nights a week too. SF institution!
Absolutely delightful meal well served in a pleasant setting. We sat in the alley outside and the weather was perfect. Our party stayed well after the meal was finished and didn't have any problems.

Its was The Place to See and Be Seen ages ago.....
Great place to run in out of the rain...
Usually much busy ...but the service and food was good on the day I went .

reviews.text: Great food and very friendly service. The fried rice and green beans were delicious. They were great dealing with food allergies. Large area still feels intimate.

Limited menu, but what they do have to offer is excellent. I had the prawn satay, which was wonderful and an interesting twist on traditional nutty satay. I had the silky chocolate cake for dessert which was sinfully delicious and worth a visit all on its own. The service was phenomenal from the moment I stepped in the door to the last bite of dessert. Nice ambience too, both for dining alone (as I was) as well as with a group.
Went for happy hour.  Great service.  Comfortable hip ambience.  Menu selections very good.  Try the dollar oysters and chicken satay. Definitely going back.
Helpful service. Interesting twists on traditional Asian/Indian cuisine. Nice ambience. Five minutes walk from Union Square. Fair pricing.

When I went to E&O, my group ordered multiple items off the menu, family style. After trying multiple things off the menu, I can confidently say that the corn fritters are the best thing about this place. I'm still craving them weeks later.

Everything else on the menu was good as well, although all of the deserts (except the ginger spice cookies) were a miss for our group. That said, you won't be disappointed with your experience here.

result.formatted_address: 375 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: DNA Lounge

reviews.text: Asked for glass of water; they said they don't give out cups and that I'd have to buy a drink.  Nickel-and-diming everything. 25% premium for tickets at the door, plus a $2 credit card fee, then $9 beers once you're inside. Booths available for purchase, which then go empty. I've always admired the owner jwz@, an open source nerd, for his cool ideas. But no wonder this place is going out of business. Really losing touch with the funky, low-key, cheap San Francisco throwback that this place is supposed to be. Not the rebellious cyberpunk haven that I expected. Now it's just a punk-ass business. I wish Jamie luck.

Came here for a 'Mortified' comedy show. The show was awesome and the DNA Lounge is a cool venue- I watched from the upper balcony and it was a little crowded but not too bad. Drinks were not super cheap but they were strong so no complaints there. I did get charger $4 for a cup of tonic water and that seemed a little steep.

One of the best clubs in town. Usually there’s a cover, ins and outs are typically fine. There’s a few rooms and stages. Sometimes a burlesque show upstairs. There is a 24 hour pizza joint in this club complex.

What a gnarly place! You will have anything from burlesque shows to electronic music in a given night. Excellent bar with a super wicked house drink. There are plenty of beers on tap too. The area multiple levels and different rooms to chill in. You really can't beat this place if you are looking for a spark. Also, they have pizza 🍕 you can get next door twenty four hours a day! Check this place out next you are in San Francisco! Plenty of street parking in the area too! Let's rock and roll 🍥
I love this place. Tons of memories, and one of my favorite venues. We come all the way from the central valley to this place. THE PIZZA IS AWESOME.

result.name: Nihon Whisky Lounge

reviews.text:
Brilliant little whiskey and sushi bar, easy 5 stars for great cocktails, delicious food and an awesome atmosphere (and music). Very cool.

Didn't know what I was doing with whisky selection but the waitress was really helpful, had an amazing rye old fashioned. Sushi was super fresh and everything else was super tasty. 👌

I know I have come on to this website before and made a statement like "this is my favorite restaurant" but fr, THIS is my favorite restaurant.

And yet... it is more than a restaurant, it's more like an experience. an experience for the heart, soul, and body for true immersion in quality, love, and discovery.

thanks

Food was good... but next time I dine solely on cocktails and whiskey! The Dead Rabbit is a fantastic Smokey whiskey take on a Last Word. Herbal, acidic, bitter, lightly sweet— sandal wood and rose dance across the palette with a Meyer touch. Could drink a gallon of that. Yknow. If ye olde liver could handle that 😝

Very good food served here with a fun trendy atmosphere. The walls of whiskey are impressive to look at. I was there on a saturday night and the music choice was awesome. Funk and R & B, great way to get the evening started. I highly recommend the Hon maguro tasting which was the freshest bluefin, Toro, akami and chutoro I've ever eaten.
Almost everything was delicious. Master bar tender really knows his whisky. Great selection.

result.formatted_address: 240 California St, San Francisco, CA 94111, USA
result.name: Tadich Grill

reviews.text: There is a reason that they have been open for so long.  There is a reason major Financial deals are negotiated over lunch at the bar. The food is perfect. The service is perfect. The drinks are frankly some of the best in the city. The atmosphere is perfect. This is a great place to celebrate any occasion.

Stumbled across this restaurant and so happy we did! Hands down our best meal while in San Francisco.  Exactly what I was hoping for as far experiencing the ambiance of San Francisco.  The food was AMAZING... this will be our go to next time we are in town!

Great spot.  Classic bar restaurant and the food is great. Probably not for everyone but definitely my kind of place.  Defines great food and bar haunt in old school style. Super pro staff here as well. Fish cooked on your choice of open flame is not to be beat. Its crowded and can be noisy but that's what I like.

Always need to plan a visit when in SF. Clam chowder and an Anchor Steam to warm you up from the Bay Chill. Excellent service, classic historic spot. Beautiful long bar makes it easy to pop-in without needing to wait for a formal table. Efficient service.

The Taddich Grill is what you might imagine SF dining was like 50 years ago. They offer a variety of fishes prepared in a few different ways: grilled, saute, pan fried or deep fried. Every plate comes with cooked seasonal veg and rice or potatoes. The fish I've had here has been pretty fresh, though somewhat under seasoned. Oh but why do I keep coming back? The ambiance exudes an old world charm that is so refreshing in this hipster-run city!The clientele is a mix of regulars, tourists, and business people coming in for a drink. The wait staff (men in white coats who have likely been working here for 10+ years) is charming yet efficient. Nothing escapes their watchful eye. They seated us at the bar in the order that we came in without taking our names down! During my meal my cup never ran dry and every condiment was brought over without asking.  Tadich is a true SF gem for old timey favorites!

reviews.text:
We enjoyed our visit here even though we had to wait about 30 minutes. The sky terrace has great view on San Francisco and the Union square in particular.
It is located on the 8th floor and you have two options: to sit on the street having spectacular view, or inside.
Birds are a bit of a problem but it is okay overall.
Parking is not a problem if you agree to pay the price.
The food is good and portions are enormous so we always take half of the order in the boxes to go.

Normally Great food, overcrowded at 3pm. Ate at the bar. The drinks looked great. 
Had a over cooked hamburger... I  know a hamburger at the Cheesecake factory?? What was I thinking? The offer was there to refuse and get something else... I guess I am not type to do that unless it is really bad.

Cheesecake Factory it's always good place to visit. Most of all I liked a view from outside patio, highly recommend to go there if weather is good. Menu is full of different foods, hard to make a choice:) hope one day they will provide menu with pictures. The only bad thing is a waiting line...

Dinner portions were very large and were fairly tasty. Menu has a very large selection, to the point where one doesn't feel like reading through everything. The cheesecake menu also has a lot of selection, but the cheesecake we had were pretty mediocre. It's still good, but not as rich or dense as one might like.

Terrible seating assistance. They gave you a device that shakes and after shake you know you will be seated. But even though our device shakes, they didn't seat us they say they call my name. I can't understand why they make that devices if they didn't use it. We waited obnoxiously because we are tourist and English is our second language. We are afraid to not catch the names. We waited almost half an hour like this and then ask they say we didn't forget you. But after another than minutes we left there because we lost out hope. Terrible attitude and business. Unbelievably bad workers.

reviews.text: I still haven’t been able to get the bartenders name but he practically knows my husband and I when we visit SF (he’s the older cat with the shaved head)Super friendly crowd every time we go. You never know who you might spark a conversation with, since everyone is so outgoing. First time we went, a guy came back with wings and shared it with the whole bar. Another guy started buying people drinks! We were hooked since then lol! The best bar I have been to by far!

I love this bar. Hands down the best little neighborhood bar in San Francisco I visited. Super atmosphere, and friendly service. This place is the real deal. I will be back every time I'm in San Francisco.
My favourite spot for a drink and sports in all of San Francisco. The bar is the perfect spot to get a great beer on tap or try a cocktail. No airs and graces just good people at a great bar.
Go Bills!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Looking for an awesome place to be when the games are on? Look no further! They have it all. Beer. TVs. And awesome people.
Great popcorn. Great service. Great drinks!

reviews.text: Shouldn't be telling you, but this place truly is a happy hour gem. Great prices on food and drinks. You can get away a drink, food, and tip for ~$12 if you need a quick fix. It's first come first server for the HH seating and is not ideal for big groups. It's really too intimate and you'll have a hard time finding enough seats for +4. Because their prices are so screaming good show up early (4:00 pm) or expect to wait.

One of the best chips in town. Orange sauce is AMAZING. Everything is pretty much on point and good. 

Dinner lines can be long, as much as an hour wait. Lunch is quicker. 

Outdoor seating along with indoor. Staff is friendly.

Great Mexican food restaurant in the Financial District tucked away on Yerba Buena lane. Great  place for lunch but if it's a weekday and you're short on time then you'll want to get there by 1130 as that's when the line starts building up. They have the menu on the wall when you walk in, you order and pay upfront and then they'll bring it to you. So you can in and out of there pretty quickly if you want to. The guacamole is great but expensive and skimpy. I ordered a large and it wasn't even really enough to share with anyone. I've been told not to order the mole here as it isn't really to par however I ordered the barbacoa last time and it was excellent.
Delicious food, great service. Seated right away outside. Chips and salsa we're so good! Tacos 🌮🌮 beans and rice we're fresh and filling.

I love this place. I’ve been here probably 5 times and am always extremely happy with the food. The last time I went I had the “salad” with prawns and was super happy. It was light, balanced, and filling. The guacamole is tasty, he chips are crispy and well salted, and I love the salsa bar. They have such a great selection of salsa. The pico and the green sauce are my favorite

result.name: In-N-Out Burger

reviews.text: Food is good for fast food. I got my burger animal style and i definitely liked it more than the original. Staff was nice and helpful in answering our questions. Location is very busy as it is right by the harbor, but we got our food quickly. There is a good amount of seating, but the amount of traffic this location gets makes it difficult to find seats during meal times.

Got a recommendation from my hotel that this was a good burger joint. The classic burger I had was the best I've had for awhile. Good atmosphere and friendly staff make this the best dining experience I've had in San Francisco.

These guys are super quick considering how busy it is! I had the hamburger combo with a vanilla shake. Burger buns are toasted and crunch inside which makes them less soggy than other chains. The sauce is great too. The fries I got were super small (I think it was the bottom of a basket) so nothing to write home about, but the shake was super thick and creamy.

Being from a state that does not have In-N-Out it is always a treat to visit one while traveling. The food is consistently well made and fresh. I like the limited menu and I know exactly what I will order before visiting. I always recommend to others who are traveling as well.

I have been enjoying In & Out Burgers for over 45 years.  They are fresh daily from the neat to the buns, and their shakes can not be beaten....The very best in the business because it remains "a family business" that cares about their reputation, their product and reasonable prices with happy, competent employees.  Treat yourself and friends and I promise you will return..  They shame the other competition with their quality, taste and service.

result.formatted_address: 25 Yerba Buena Ln, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
result.name: Amber

reviews.text: I've always liked this little cluster of restaurants in the Yerba Buena area because it seems a bit more serene from the hustle of market street and is quite nice overall. I stopped in after work with a friend as we both heard great reviews of Amber. As it is an Indian restaurant, the strong Indian spice smell immediately wafted in your face. The restaurant had nice decor and was a bit dimly lit so it would make for a great date spot. My friend and I started off with an order of the naan. It was quite good as isn't wasn't too oily and was a good accompaniment to the sauces in our entrees. We got a curry lamb dish and a curry chicken dish which were both excellent. The portions were really generous too as we had leftovers to go.  Other than a lingering smell on our clothes after the dinner, the overall food and experience were great.

Very tasty food, however vibe was a little flat. Our plates arrived after our neighbours had finished eating, even though we ordered before them. But was very well redeemed with a complimentary glass of wine!

I've passed this restaurant on numerous occasions. It's a shame that I've gone so long not enjoying this wonderful place! While visiting San Francisco, I encourage you to make the right decision and try the Butter Chicken (one of the best I've ever had).

Not only was the food top notch, but the service was terrific. Our waitress Galina and the supporting staff all contributed to a great evening.

I'll be visiting this location again on my next trip to San Francisco.
Great ambience and location. Hard to find a parking nearby even on weekdays. Great presentation. Chicken curry was at its best. Kulfi and mango brûlée was unbeatably delicious.

I stopped here because of the great reviews, but although the food was pretty good, there were a few things that caught me off guard that made me give this place a 3:

Mango Juice was very obviously watered down.  Two people got a glass, and we both independently noticed that there was water added to the juice.  It didn't mix well, and half the glass ended up as mostly water in the end.

The dishes didn't come with rice.  A saag dish isn't eaten without rice, yet it didn't come with rice by default.  I had to order an extra dish of rice at $4 per dish, whereas it should've come with a little rice.  I've never been to an Indian restaurant where rice wasn't served with the main dish (even if you ordered a dry dish), so it was irritating not only to have to wait an extra 5-10 minutes for a bowl of rice to come out, but to have to pay extra for something that is culturally standard for the food.

Other than those two things, the service and food was 4/5, ambiance was  5/5, and the value for the meal was 2/5.

reviews.text: I really don’t see why this place is so hyped up! First, you most always have to wait in a long line outside just to get your foot in the door. Our wait was almost two hours in the cold! So we’re thinking the food must be good here, right? Wrong. The breakfast was just average at best. Service from the staff was fine, but average food taste and presentation. Three stars.

This is an amazing place. We have been coming here for a decade and still love it. We always brings friends from out of the country here. Please know the line is crazy but totally worth the waiting. Bring your latte and newspaper and enjoy the sun while you are waiting.

The longest I've ever queued for a meal! Get there early while the queue is short otherwise you'll spend a while waiting - we nearly got to 2 hours. However, once you're inside, it's relatively speedy and the staff are helpful. The french toast is amazing and all the food is prepared and presented very well. (This was from a visit in September 2015 so it may well have changed now.)

We LOVED this place. Not only is the food outstanding but the customer service was excellent as well. We enjoyed The Farmer omelet, which is packed with delicious goat cheese and a special they had, the Dungeness crab omelet. Both were excellent. We also loved the homemade jam and sourdough baguette that comes with your meal!  This place is a local and tourist favorite, so it's apparently always packed but they are very organized and serve the food quickly once you're seated. Well worth the wait in my opinion!

My wife and I only had one morning in San Fran and I'm so glad we waited in line for this place. Mama's breakfast sandwich was INCREDIBLE! I haven't had a breakfast that good in a very long time. SO worth the wait! Nice employees and cute little sitting area. You won't regret coming here.

result.name: The Big 4

reviews.text:
A true San Francisco classic.
Elegant, great service-that is  old-school, lovely ambiance
and an excellent menu. This is not the restaurant you whip out your iPhone to take pictures of the food. As famous for their brunch as their lunch and their dinner menu. Once, along time ago, my date was not allowed in because he didn't have a tie ... The dress code has changed.

After visiting San Fran for many years, we finally remembered to make a dinner reservation at The Big 4 before arriving in town.  The restaurant is so named for the four industrialists who were responsible for SF's early growth and success.  Many photos and artifacts are on display much like a museum.  The decor is gorgeous wood paneled walls, large antique mirrors, burgandy velvet banquettes, candle light,  fine linens and restaurant silver, impeccably mannered staff attend almost invisibly while making guests feel like royals.  The menu is heavily weighted towards aged, prime steak and chops.  Sides are family style, order several.  Desserts are decadent.  Enjoy live piano music, and arrive early to spend time in the bar before dinner for a full Big 4 experience.  We can't wait to return for another luxurious experience in this gorgeous building.
Great place. Beautiful piano playing created an incredible atmosphere.
Highly suggest this place for a drink. The decor and atmosphere is great include the drinks
Great food and nice ambiance

reviews.text: Our party of six was seated as soon as we arrived (reservation made on Open Table) and we had a great table by the window. The service was excellent and the food options were explained and the suggestions were well received. From the cocktails to the starters to the entrees and dessert, everything was delicious and prepared perfectly! With six of us we were able to try many different things. I loved the potato-crusted salmon the most, but everything I ate was tasty. We never felt rushed during the meal and the server was attentive but not overbearing. Water glasses were always full and the food was perfectly timed to arrive together and just as the previous course was ending. I had budgeted about $100 for the meal and with two cocktails, starters, an entree and dessert I stayed right on target. I would definitely return - it was the perfect pre-theater dining experience!
Great place for brunch. Its located with many other restaurants. I had yummy yummy french toast and classic margarita.  I would definitely vouch for that. Parking could be a challenge.
I had a meal here and I couldn't stop talking about it for the next few days. Great food and cozy atmosphere. Always great service.
Excellent bar. The drink menu and bar staff deliver memorable delicious cocktails. The food also is rich with flavor. Really good oysters, french onion soup. A must if you're in the area.

Yum! Stopped here for some drinks and apps before heading to the Symphony with my girls. We were running late (fancy clothes takes more time!) and the server at the bar was quick attentive and helpful with a speedy check. Cocktails were fabulous, apps we're creative twists on classics. Fried garbanzos didn't last a minute on the plate! Nom!

result.name: John's Grill

reviews.text: This place is so cool. Food is overall fantastic, nice service. The building is awesome. Definitely an "old-school" city feel. They've even got probably hundreds of portraits of San Francisco Police captains, lieutenants, and inspectors up on the wall. Overall it's just a really unique restaurant. Highly recommend it.

I'm by no means a critic but here are my opinions. 

Ambience:
Sitting down the jazz was obnoxiously loud meaning the people sat across the walkway to me had to near-on scream at each other to be heard... meaning I had screaming couple vs overly loud jazz...  Not a good start.
This restaurant also isn't the kind of place you sit down and enjoy a slow meal (which is my preference), it comes across more rushed and a more in'n'out kind of joint which came through in the service. 

Meal:
The steak was OK... I've had amazing steak and I've had good steak,  this for me was just below the latter of the two with a lot of fat that could have been trimmed but wasn't. 

The dessert was the star of the show. Which for me sets a great restaurant apart from an OK restaurant. A great restaurant will wow you throughout the meal; an OK restaurant will make sure you leave on a good note.

Excellent Filet Mignon and Heirloom Tomato Salad. The server​ was very polite, knowledgeable and fast. Very quick service from time of order for this type of restaurant. Really nice retro atmosphere. The Clam Chowder was among the best I have ever had.

I'm from the Midwest. I know and well appreciate corn fed Midwestern steak. The problem is finding it because they ship most of good stuff out. John's Grill apparently is responsible for some of that shortage. My steak was excellent. Great taste, tender and cooked correctly. The service was good and fast. San Francisco isn't my favorite city but John's certainly is on my list of favorite steakhouses where I thought I might otherwise starve in need of a good steak.

I go here EVERY TIME I'm in San Francisco.  The Jack LaLaine's Favorite Salad is all I ever order. It's fabulous!  The restaurant has the original Maltese Falcon from the movie.  The waitstaff is wonderful, the drinks are so good, and the atmosphere takes you back.

reviews.text: Thank you Super Duper Burgers for one of the best meals in San Francisco! Who knew I would actually enjoy a $10 burger more than dishes at a Michelin star restaurant. I absolutely loved my chicken sandwich. I added the jack cheese topping for $0.5. The garlic fries were tasty, too. I hope they expand to Canada!

Oh my god. These burgers are like no other!  The flavor is unbelievable and their toppings are simple.  They've also got super yummy shakes that aren't too sweet.   Good stuff, and most certainly not like any other burger.

This is my new favorite place to get a chicken sandwich and vanilla cone! You can truly taste the quality and freshness. My favorite is the chicken sandwich with bacon, cheese, extra grilled onions, and all the usual lettuce, tomato, sauce, etc. The chipotle sauce really adds a nice kick to it. Service is usually fast, although there have been times I've come in after lunch rush and still waited a while. This location is long, but narrow, and seating is limited. They have a few tables on the side as you walk in, and they also have a small upstairs area. My only complaint is the price. For one chicken sandwich and a regular vanilla cone, it comes out to $15. That doesn't even include fries. They say on their website that they use fresh, locally sourced ingredients, and that's why they're more expensive, but come on. They do have very tasty food though, and the donuts are good too. I have been visiting this place several times a week for the past couple weeks.
I've eaten here thrice and have never had a bad meal.  I've had the beef and the bison burgers and the fries are definitely worth it.  Enjoy.

Stopped in here after the D-backs game. Love the ambiance. We had the IPA bacon which was a very nice start. Also ordered the 3 sliders.. Korean and BBQ brisket. Both are excellent. I do wish they had more bottle of wines, either way I will be back!

reviews.text: Best steak house we've been to, and we've been to a lot. Let's start with the service, from the moment you walk in they're friendly and inviting and are on top of their game. The wait staff takes over once you're seated without missing a beat, and takes interest in all areas of your experience. They had a three course special paired with wine that was absolutely delicious, and took the time to explain each dish, the ingredients and why the wine was chosen to accompany the dish.  We choose Epic for a special occasion, and they blew it out of the water. On top of it all, we were sat right next to a window with one of the best views of the bridge. If you're thinking about trying out Epic, go for it, you'll love it.

Excellent views.  Very fresh and briny oysters.  Good wine suggestion from wait staff.  Had dinner in communal area of bar.  Incredibly almost impossibly fast service.  NY strip with peppercorn and coffee rub was flavorful and juicy.  Only stop from 5 stars was medium rare closer to medium, but this may be from experience in NY where everything is errs on rare side.  This steak was robably what most people at home call medium rare, but lots of steak houses call medium.  It was still delicious, but order rare if you really want cool center.  Steak was really tasty, just need to know what is expected where you order.  NY tends toward less cooked and I was just used to that.

Excellent steaks and great location. Very expensive, but you are paying for the location and an exceptionally well made steak. They know how to do a good Pittsburgh blue, and when you order sides, they are quite large portions. The quality of the meat seemed very high and the tenderness of the rib-eye was perfect.

I picked a great night to take my wife out for her bday. It was 70 outside and we were able to sit on the out door patio, even ask them to turn the outdoor heater off. Drinks were stiff and great. Food was awesome prime rib was a must for myself, my wife had a butterflyed steak as she likes it a bit more cooked on the inside. The sides dishes were good as well. No dessert was ordered. Valet was $20 and quick to retrieve our car. All around it was a great time and place. Pricey but I know that going into it.

I always enjoy my meals here, and I don't even eat red meat! The veggie sides are great and there's usually one or two nice vegetarian/pescatarian starter dishes on the menu that are filling enough to make a meal. Great cocktails, lovely ambiance, plus a stellar view of the Bay bridge make it worth the splurge for a special occasion. The also have a great weekend brunch!

reviews.text: The best burrito in San Francisco. Every bite is amazing and doesn't feel very heavy and filling after finishing the burrito that is just over a foot long. Meat is cooked fresh and service was quick and organized even when it was very crowded. I love this place, I wish I could eat this burrito every day!

Not much more to say; this place does everything right in terms of Mission Burritos: delicious and large burritos at a very affordable price. The fresh avocado in the super burritos only adds to an already great burrito. As long as the line isn't too far our the door the wait isn't long.

It is open til 3:30am and a block from BART for late night eats. Cash only.

Bring cash because they don’t accept anything else.   They are open until 3:30am.  It’s not in the best neighborhoods so make sure you have nothing in sight in your car or the homeless people will break your window.    And they are bold they broke the window of a car in front of mine and didn’t care that I was looking them.   The food was good and the price was right.  And the line was long but they were quick.   Hope this helps ;)

One of the best taquerias in the mission, very tasty and large burritos that won't leave you feeling ill post eat. Great homemade salsas. Bathroom looks a bit like a murder scene which is par for the course. Highly recommend this place for a stop in your tour of mission burritos.

I love El Farolito! Been there three times and have never had a bad experience. It's the authentic food and atmosphere I've been craving since moving here from Chicago. Hours are also excellent - satisfied 1 AM cravings last night. Long story short - this place is *the best*.

reviews.text: TERRIBLE!!! After LOVING the Gracias Madre in LA, we were super excited to try the SF spot but unfortunately, it was very disappointing! It felt like we were in a bad, fast food joint & we couldn't wait to get out of there! First off, I made a reservation days before but when we arrived, we were told "all of our seats are communal" (even if you make a reservation).  Had I known that, we would never have gone there to begin with.  So we opted for the bar, which is basically in the kitchen so those seats sucked too!  As for the food - the menu was nothing like the LA menu (which I found strange) but whatever, we went with it.  I ordered chips & salsa & when we opened the basket of chips, there was just a handful of chips for 2 of us. When I asked if this was all we would get, I was told "that's it".  So we ordered 2 appetizers (which were gross) & 2 sparkling lemonades and it came to $51.  This place SUCKS & we'll never be back!

This is authentic vegan food! I love the creativity and flavor of the food. The staff is very attentive. The atmosphere is open and inviting. The restrooms are clean. This place is doing a good job! I'd definitely go back.

The food here was awesome and definitely flavorful. The place was cozy and all the people working there were smiling, which gave the place a really good vibe. They don't seem to over crowd the place so it was easy to hold a conversation with someone sitting next to you.

Even on a Tuesday night it was full at 8:30, and with a reservation for two, sat at a communal table. My dining companion is a carnivore, and was relatively satisfied, but not converted. I enjoyed the tamale with the cashew crema. The Bowl Dos was very full of spinach and pineapple salsa, but could use more rice.  The guacamole was a bit bland, but that seems to be the trend in SF. The tortilla chips were nicely house-fried. I'd prefer a tequila margarita with this kind of meal, but they serve sake drinks, wine and beer.

I tried a number of menu options and would have been entirely underwhelmed if it wasn't for the Eggplant Tacos. They had a freshness and richness that the other dishes lacked. Of all the things I tried they're the only ones I'd return for. Otherwise the staff were great and the atmosphere was nice. The menu could do with a bit of a refresh

reviews.text: Amazing meal.  Everything was so good.  Really excited to hear that everything on the brunch menu except the French toast could be made vegan.  Vegan hash was excellent! Vegan banana chocolate cake with coconut sorbet was incredibly good.  Highly recommend for outstanding vegan dining experience!!

HOLY DELICIOUSNESS!!! I have spent 23 years as a vegetarian with mostly subpar food that has become a norm. I just...don't look for much flavor! Thai and Indian dishes are usually ones that call my name. But HELLO AMAZING! We went to Greens and my tastebuds were awakened for the first time! I had the Green Curry but also tried their sweet potato dish and the filo dough (just bites from others). Each bite was infused with FLAVOR (something that most vegetarians forget that exists in such exquisite detail!). I cannot wait to go back. Take my money!
We have been going here for over 20 years. First time gluten free and they were able to accommodate. Great views, especially from window seats, but you may need to wait for that

Great food and beautiful atmosphere.
Most of the ingredients are sourced locally, making the whole experience even more special.
Try to get a table near the windows facing the marina and Bay area.
Specially beautiful towards the end of the day.

Make sure to make a reservation just to be safe. We went on a popular night and had to wait even with a reservation. Delicious vegan and vegetarian options. Knowledgeable and friendly staff. Love the decor.

reviews.text:
Very happy, warm place. Staff are dressed up in traditional clothing and beaming, seeming keen to ensure you have a good time with your friends. HUGE beer selection as well as a nice succinct menu. So far, everything I've had there has been top notch. 

Prices on the entrees can be a bit high, and I often come out spending more than I expected to, simply because we stay longer than we planned. Desserts as well were mildly disappointing, although they're clearly made on-site which I always appreciate. 

This will be a go-to for me when I have groups of friends looking to have a meal, a drink, and a good time.

This place had a warm and authentic ambience, with a great selection of Belgian and German beers, and French wines. The food and dessert were very different from what I have ever tasted. The meat was well cooked and was falling from the bones. The servers were very polite and gave us some good recommendation for the dinner.

Great schnitzel and beer make for a tasty meal. The warm, cozy ambiance is welcoming and comfortable. Don't order a boot (3L) of beer unless you're ready for your night to be over and have a safe way to get home! A great place to celebrate Oktoberfest!

Had a new bartender who did know anything about the menu or drinks, and I had to repeat every order at least 3 times. Food and drinkbwere good. Need to update the menu because a few deserts are no longer available.

Food was okay, not worth the price.  Service was fine, until it wasn’t and staff interceded, presumably out of boredom, in a private family matter and tried to convince my 70 year old mother that I was in danger after leaving restaurant.  I wouldn’t make this up, they convinced her to call police.  I don’t know what they were thinking, but the mediocre short ribs lost what little luster the hurried presentation had mustered after that.  Boo.

Lovely view of the bay if you sit outside, comfortable bar seating if you stay in.

reviews.text:
Great Pizza w/ a reasonable wait time located in a nice SF location.  Stopped here for lunch cause it's on so many lists and I was not disappointed.  The menu is full of so many pizza options that I already have a plan to return for more pizza!  We ended up getting 2 different types of pizza and both were quite good.  The service was a little slow, but not overly so.  The outdoor sitting was nice but that's because it was a beautiful day for it :)

If you love pizza, you should definitely give this place a shot.

We've now been to Tony's a few times, getting different styles of pizza and appreciating it so much for its taste and quality. Some consider this to be the best overall pizza place in the US. Maybe, I don't know. I do know that it's excellent and worth going more than once. I will definitely return. Oh, but be prepared to waaaait.

Feb. 2018
Any one of their pizzas may not be "the best" pizza --- although all the ones I've tried have been excellent and I especially enjoy the Trenton style --- Tony's has a large and diverse selection of top-notch pizza and therefore may be the best overall pizza restaurant in the world.

Ok, let me start off by saying that everyone has their own opinion of the best pizza.  I mean everyone has their own opinion of everything in general, but pizza is one of those things that almost everyone has a different opinion on.  As far as this place goes, it's one of the few times that I've brought people here from across the country, and they've agreed that it was almost as good as being bombarded by puppies.  They have so many different kinds of pizzas here and I've yet to have anything that I don't like.  The sauces are so delicious, the toppings range from classic cheese and pepperoni, to I have no clue what the hell that is but I'm gonna eat it anyway because it sounds delicious. The crust, good god the crust, definitely the best part, especially the Sicilian style.  It is a thicker crust, but so light and super crunchy on the bottom. If you're a fan of meatballs, get them.  You will not be sorry if you do.  The only real bad thing about this place is that you will wait.  If you come on a weekend for dinner, just put your name down and go wander the wharf for a while because you're gonna have a few hours to burn.  If you've got the time though, try it.  There's a reason people are still willing to go through the 2.5+ hour waits to eat here.

Pizza was mediocre, service was terrible.  Had to wait 45 minutes, but the waiting area was full.  Once seated waited 30 Minutes for anyone to take our order.  Had to find waitress, who said they forgot to assign the table, but didn’t apologize.  Asked waitress to turn up the table heater (we were outside), but she said it was only one setting. Another waiter later told us it wasn’t turned on. Didn’t see waitress for the entire meal.  Water was not refilled. Waitress was rude at end of service, brought us the wrong bill then gave out a big sigh crumpled it up and walked off.  Pizza was average, overpriced, crust was bland and undercooked for Neapolitan.

Wow, really good pizza. Been craving some thin crust wood oven pizza, and this place hits the spot.  Came here with one other friend and we barely finished the New Yorker. The price is a bit steep for pizza, but well worth it for some really really good pie.

reviews.text: This restaurant lives up to its reputation as one of the best steak houses in San Francisco. I highly recommend it for anyone looking for a place to take a colleague or a date. The ambiance is warm and professional and the steak is delicious. They specialize in aged meat and Japanese delicacies such as Wagyu beef. It’s a must-see while visiting or for locals.

A friend invited me to Alexander's Steakhouse. I was hesitant as a vegan because... well it's a steakhouse! But the staff accommodated my requests and even gave me and my friend (non-veg) special items just for us.
The food was delicious, atmosphere was upscale, staff were attentive and friendly. The food was unique as it was visually appealing.

excellent service (really, really good kind), excellent drinks and expansive wine menu, some incredibly food (especially appetizers and steaks).  so why 4 stars?  because I wouldn't go there if I'm paying - I'd go to Cockscomb and Marlowe nearby.  having said that, my first choice for business meals.
Nice atmosphere. Good steaks, very little options if you're not a lover of red meat. Small non-steak portions. Bring your own wine. Over priced for the value .

Ambiance was nice. We had our own space which was nice. Super warm and friendly staff. The hamachi shots were sooooo good. It took awhile for us get the meal course so I wasn’t as hungry and didn’t finish it. I wasn’t a big fan of the dessert either. Overall good experience.

I only got a pizza here so I can't judge the rest of the menu.
Pizzas are good, but you should know that if you are looking for a thin crust pizza, like a napolitain style or a new york style pizza, you should keep walking.
Here the pizza have a thick, bread like crust, and a comforting amount of cheese!
I kind of enjoyed it but it's definitely on the heavy side of the pizza world.
Now that you know what kind of pizza to expect, I can say that it's good pizza, crunchy crust, flavorful tomato sauce, nice amount of cheese and a lot of crust to chew on!
The pizza here is amazing! It's a bit expensive but very tasty. It's definitely worth it though.
They use only the cheapest rubbery mozzarella and heap it on their pies. They should be run out of North Beach.

reviews.text: Holy prime rib heaven! If you love prime rib then you have to go here. Not only is the prime rib amazing but the salad is also to die for. They have a good drink menu and decent wine selection. My husband gets us reservations every year for my birthday. I'm still trying to convince him that we should also celebrate my half birthday here but I haven't succeeded.

House of Prime Rib is a classic for SF locals and tourists alike.  We came here recently for a birthday and had a great time.  The menu has a minimum number of choices you have to make so its easy on the indecisive pickers.  The prime rib was very flavorful (though my particular piece was a little fatty) and the service was theatrical, fun, yet attentive.  They took a picture of our group, framed it and gave it to my mom which she thought was the coolest thing ever.  I would recommend this place for celebrations, but the food has been the same probably for 50 years so if you're looking for something exciting and innovative, there are better options.

Love the food and the service was great.  We will definitely return several times a year.
However it would be awesome if  they could improve by adding some type of sound absorbing material as the dining rooms can get really loud.   So, while this is not a quiet romantic place, the menu is great if you are a prime rib lover.   The drinks are good.   The meat is excellent.   And the rest of the experience is pretty solid.

Delicious prime rib, wonderful experience. You get exactly what you'd expect here - old school vibe, classic cocktails, and great meat. The king's cut was definitely too much food, but in a good way. We loved watching the carvers work their magic and our server was excellent. The creamed corn was delicious and the mashed potatoes were generally better than the baked potato, but that's to be expected.

It's good but not great. The menu is limited but they do it well. The atmosphere is decent especially for such a busy place. The service was fine but the staff wasn't really friendly. House of Prime Rib is worth going to once if you live here or visit often. Not sure that I would go back again.

reviews.text:
Had an amazing chocolate kouign ammann here, it was crisp and yummy. They also have other interesting dessert collection. It is a nice place to spend a weekend morning having coffee with loved ones.
If you are planning to visit the place on weekends, prepare to wait in a line. The employees are pretty quick, so wait time is not long.
Yummy croissants..especially the banana almond chocolate one. Yummy tartine  (open faced sandwiches). Cool art on wall  and beautiful flower arrangements. A gem of a place!
Always delicious pasties! My favorite being the chocolate & banana croissant and the ham & cheese croissant. Make sure to ask for them heated up! It's worth the 10 min wait
Recommended to us by family it was THE highlight of our SF trip. Lunch was amazing, staff helpful and courteous and the treats phenomenal. We will always stop here when in the city
This place has some amazing bakery items. Very good for breakfast. It is usually very busy, so in case you want to grab a spot, try to reach by 7:00am

reviews.text: It's IHOP, what can you ask for beyond delicious pancakes, tasty bacon and more food for the buck than any "trendy" restaurant? The eggs were over buttered (felt oily), but the taste was great! Can't help but wish I had waited for the unlimited pancakes, but couldn't help myself!

Busy place because of being so close to Fisherman's Wharf.  Took a while to be seated but service was good. Good tasted better than other IHOP's I've been too. May have been the weather and being with good company. Overall, very good experience.

ihop is the place to go for breakfast if there's one near you. Cooked breakfast then pancakes to finish, all with juice and coffee and teas. Staff happy to help with all you need. 4 syrup' s on the table for you to top up whilst diving into the lush pancakes.

One of nicer breakfast place in US. The service staffs were attentive to your needs keep asking if the coffee needs refill, sauces is enough etc. They have a huge range of pancakes, omelettes and crepes. Children meals are available. They also provide 4 types of syprus, blue berry, strawberry, peacan and old fashion. It is waking distance from various hotels like Sheraton, Marriot, Holiday Inn Express etc. Do go early as the crowds is coming fast at 9am onwards.

This is a the best place to relax and sit down with love ones have a nice meal laughs and much more the location is the best near to the ship terminals. This my second time eating and I love it. Taste

reviews.text:
Another SF food landmark. A well made taqueria with a huge selection of Mexican dishes, a salsa bar that enough for me to stay and if you're lucky to see a Mariachi band play songs while enjoying tacos and burritos.

Been a regular for years and the tastes never changed. There's no way to compare fast food tacos from an authentic Mission style burritos of Pancho Villa.

One of the cleanest and freshest mexideli in the city. I love I can get a burrito, nachos, or a salad here and know everything is really fresh. 
My only complaint is because they are so busy, service can take a little longer, especially when they have a lot of to go orders. 
The staff are usually very friendly, and put up with my Spanglish. 
It's my go to for Mexican in the hood.

The food was great! The lines were long but well worth it. By the time we got our food ordered, we had seats! It was very crowded and noisy, but are combination plates for fantastic! I recommend the chicken enchilada dinner.

Recommended to us by a friend who lives in the area and,  THANK GOODNESS we asked!   This place is constantly busy leading to super fresh,  yet fast food.  We were so impressed with the politeness of the staff,  the freshness and absolute deliciousness of the food and affordability that we can't wait to visit on our next trip.   
Really close to the BART station at Mission and just 3 away from Embarcadero.   
Do yourself a favor and go!

Excellent burritos! Quick wait time and very reasonable price (~$9 for a burrito with meat, guacamole, rice, the whole 9 yards). Casual place with a bunch of tables if you want to eat there, or great for take out. Highly recommend it!

We had the Brussels sprouts, Caesar salad and grilled octopus: everything was absolutely delicious ! Washed it down with a glass of zinfandel . Service was good.We sat at the bar, which was very comfortable. Overall, fabulous experience !
All around some delicious pastas. The Brussels sprouts are also delicious.
A very good place to grab dinner if you're in the financial district.

I love Chipotle but skip this one and walk two blocks farther to the other one in Union Square. The Westfield rent must be high because the servings here are tiny!
Nice food and cool staff

0 stars for listening to what I ask for, 2 stars for food quality, 1 star because there's always someone there that tries to make it right. When I ask for ingredients, I get the wrong ones. Associate beside her wrapped my burrito and left it where i had to reach across for it. I know working at fast food sucks, but customer service should be used no matter what.

reviews.text: This place was the worst strip club that i have been to and i travel the county. They had the nerve to charge 26 dollars to boot. If i could leave no stars i would. The girls were crooks only interested in making buck.

I came for the boobs. chicken boobs. 

For reals though, I did come for their fried chicken. They have a lunch buffet on the weekdays that is free with a $5 entrance free. And let me tell you, it was worth. I was pretty surprised by how good the buffet was. Great salad, fruit salad, chicken, beef/pork? and sides! The foodie in me was rejoicing, it's such a steal! You do have to pay extra for drinks.

Aside from the food, you also get entertainment! The ladies were great and I have to admit, it was fun sitting by the stage. Definitely finish your food before sitting by the stage, makes it harder for the ladies to do their thing if you have food and drinks on the table ;)

The establishment itself is pretty classy. I really liked the stage with the interactive background.  There are several small 2-person tables and a couple of booths on the side and an upstairs section. I didn't get to see to much since the place was a little dim in general. 

Would I come back? Yes! I really enjoyed my lunch and the staff/girls were welcoming :)

TIP: Bring that ca$h money and an appetite!

One bucket, two buckets, you can truly have as much of the delicious chicken as you want at one of the finest buffets in San Francisco. Have to disagree with some of the other reviewers though - girls are definitely slightly above average to above average. Saw some wild feats of athleticism that really blew me away. A MUST VISIT.

result.name: Zero Zero

reviews.text: A fantastic place! These guys donate to my kids hockey team and I have been there ever since.  A great local place where you can get a quick drink with a friend and the food options are excellent the bartenders and you can always find a friendly face.  I would recommend this for out-of-towners as well as local San Francisco books to find themselves downtown.
This place is super close to home so we have been going a bunch. Including my last birthday dinner. Great pizza, great wine, great dessert menu. Worth a visit for sure!

Five of us went for pizza and salad. We walked in on a Sat night at 6 without reservations. The hostess told us that she would seat us, but we would have to leave by 8:30! Not sure what that was about. I would give the crust 4 stars, but the marinara maybe a 3 star at most. The Waiter forgot to bring the salad. The only reason I am giving this place a 4 star is because when we asked about the salad, the Waiter gave it to us on the house. The salad came after we were done eating, but it was good.

We didn't make a reservation and there were no tables available the night we were there, but we were able to sit at the bar. The bartender was very attentive and we got it food quickly. The bruschetta avocado toast appetizer was very good and we also enjoyed our Fillmore pizza.

I highly recommend this place. A small note, for those with children with picky taste; this is not for them. The place is two story and has an rich dark wood decor to it. The drinks are amazing, and the food is.. mouthwatering delicious. Order an appetizer, a second plate, and finish off with a pizza. Great place; especially for a party of two. I can't wait to go back.

result.name: The Monk's Kettle

reviews.text: Intimate, cool, casual vibe yet small vibe at Monks Kettle. There's not a lot of food variety, but pretzel appetizer is really good - the sauces make it. Good variety of beers to pick from. Not a lot of wines at all. You can still have a good conversation with the noise level.

Very knowledgeable bartenders and wait staff - they really know their food and beverages. The kitchen is always spot on; I've never had a food misstep in 10 visits! Not many places can be a craft brew destination AND. provide consistently good food for people just wanting to dine. Well done Monk's Kettle.

We have been really into sours lately and Monk's kettle did not disappoint. After describing our preferences (stronger, darker sours in the Belgian style) to the bartender, she recommended two that were bottled in 375ml and both were on point! We also got some mussels and fries to share to round out a fun evening. Only drawback is that this place gets packed and you might be told to wait outside for a bar spot.

They have a great selection of beers on tap that run the length of the bar. The food, while not inexpensive, is not over priced for San Francisco. It is rather small so if it is busy expect a wait. It is all hard surfaces so when it does get busy it is very loud and hard to hear. We were seated at the bar by the door which is fine except when the door man holds it open for minutes at a time in winter.

fantastic selection of beers, and one of the best burgers in SF.  it's not a large place so it gets crowded easily.. a great spot for a late-night drink and bite.  the staff is friendly and knowledgeable. there is a tv that shows sporting events, but it's not at all a sports bar.

reviews.text:
Foreign Cinema was an amazing restaurant experience. The food was very unique, the ambience was very romantic, and the quality of the ingredients was outstanding. 

The pasta was really good and creamy - would definitely recommend that. The calamari was quite unique - definitely worth a try.

You need to book for brunch and line up at 1040 before the 11am opening if you go on the weekend. Very interesting menu split between egg cookery entres and lighter fresh appetizers. Good wine and drink options even for the Champagne snob like me. Someone here knows their wines and food. S great upper class brunch option in a friendly communal setting. The courtyard is where it's at.
Cool spot great service. The good was good and price is not bad. Perfect place for a date. The waiter was nice and thoughtful.

Great space for an office event. The servers came around with tons of great apps and the bartenders were available to make delicious cocktails. Combined with a coat check up front made the night really nice and easy

Our waiter Juan was fantastic.  Offered pairings with our drinks that were outstanding. More on that later.

Ambiance is fantastic. We sat on the patio that has a movie playing.  Charming lights and of course plenty of heaters so you don't get cold.  

When you first arrive you walk down a candle lit corridor.  It sets the mood very nicely.  

The food was delicious.  We started with a pear endive salad with a frise, blue cheese and vinaigrette dressing.

Thier curried honey glazed fried chicken was great.  I sampled my partners meal.  I had the duck that was perfect.  

Serving portions were perfect and was a top choice while dining in SF.  Get yourself a reservation.

reviews.text:
The Sycamore is a different take on bottomless brunch. I'm used to it being kinda fancy (and expensive), but the Sycamore is super casual, and not nearly as pricey.

Bottomless mimosas were $12 with $10 minimum of food. We got the mix 'n match sliders: two fried chicken sliders, a lamb burger, and the ground beef. The chicken slider was pretty rich. It was good, but I liked the ground beef better. It packed a lot of flavor into that tiny burger. My date preferred his lamb burger to the chicken.

Our glasses were frequently refilled, and the staff was fun and friendly. They had great music, lots of 80s hits. I'd go back again.
Great dive bar.   Pretty spacious patio out back for nice days. Los of tasty beers- but only beer.

Great for brunch and Charlie (if he still works there) is amazing. They have an outdoor area. You can smoke there. Their beer selection and food are good, but the wait for the bathroom can be a pain! On another note, once, the patrons in the outdoor patio, joined in with my friends and sang happy birthday to me, so this place is a special one, particularly because of that.
Hole in the wall vibe, brunch is pretty good, bottomless mimosas for $14! Gets pretty busy, it's open seating so first come first served, they also have an outdoor seating area out back.
Try the Brussel Sprouts! Great selection of beers with some very unique options.

result.name: Gary Danko

reviews.text:
A REAL GEM. 

We’ve been fortunate to enjoy many nice restaurants throughout the USA, Canada (especially Montreal), Europe especially France, Italy, Spain, and Finally Asia.

Gary Danko ranks among some of the better and certainly is one of the nicer restaurants in the greater Bay Area.

Do yourself a favor—book a reservation. You won’t be disappointed. Yet, Americans—don’t be in a hurry. Savor the food, wine and service. The service is spot on—I just sometimes see Americans in a rush and not enjoying dining. You’ll want to enjoy every second here.  

A real Gem. Thank you Gary Danko.

Amazing service and delicious food, worthy of their Michelin star. Every item I have tried was as beautiful to the eyes as it was pleasing to the  pallet. In addition to their regular menu, they have a vegetarian special menu. For a Michelin star rated restaurant the price is quite reasonable. After the meal, they have a special dessert to go. Gary Danko is my favorite restaurant in the SF Bay area.

Amazing food and wonderful atmosphere.   We went here to celebrate our marriage on our honeymoon and it did not disappoint.  All of the food just melted in our mouths.  The attention to the combination of flavours was great.  The service was wonderful as well.  We definitely recommend!
Food and service was spectacular!  Highly recommended.... especially the Louisiana butter cake dessert

Good food and decent service. But for a one Michelin star restaurant, they do not stack up. Couple of times they spilled water on our table or dropped food. Two of the items in my four course menu was just average. It's not expensive so it is good value but I expected more from a Michelin star restaurant.

result.name: State Bird Provisions

reviews.text: One of the best dining experiences of my life. Wonderful service, amazing flavors, delightful experience. We were seated at the bar which was surprisingly comfortable, and only ate off the dim sum style carts they brought around. We were full after sharing about 12 plates between two of us and sharing a half dessert- it was perfect! On a Thursday night in January we didn't have reservations so arrived about 50 minutes early and waited in line outside with a handful of others, crossing our fingers. It was actually a fun experience- watching through the window while they prepped. Obviously we got lucky and it was more than well worth the wait!!

I didn't come here for regular dinner service because it's really impossible to snag dinner reservations.   I would love to come back here for an actual sit down dinner.   My friend and I got tickets for their cook book release party which was basically easy whatever they're serving and add much as you like with 4 options for drinks (wine and sparkling wine).  No formal tables add we walked around and grabbed food for a few tables or as staff walked by with trays.   Every thing was delicious.   I think we had about 8 different dishes that night.

We had booked a table for 4 and we had to wait around 40 minutes. The host did not manage the situation well and seemed stressed so much so that he left and as new diners came in they thought we were the hosts.
I did not like the food. Most dishes tasted of cheese and salt without much flavour.
The good rating of this restaurant makes me think how different we all are. We were in SF on holiday and we invited our local friends for what we thought was a foodie treat but we were all disappointed.  We enjoyed the night out with our friends but no thanks to this restaurant.

It is now my favorite restaurant in the city. The service is great very accommodating, and the concept is really appreciable. I had a very good impression about the food it was just superb!! 

It is a good spot for dates too. I think this is the most wonderful restaurant in San Francisco.  

As a tourist, I really recommend this restaurant to visitors it is worth of your time.

This place is a great experience, an American-Asian fusion dim sum restaurant. The food here never disappoints if you are able to get a reservation. It may be a bit pricey for the little bites of food you receive, but keep in mind that they put in incredible amount of effort in getting the flavor and presentation just right. Highly recommend for those who are on the fence

reviews.text: A hip and up and coming place, with a long history, that is great for an intimate date or a young crowd.  It could be a very romantic place, but the atmosphere was more robust and energetic (as you would expect in an Irish pub).  Our waitress was sociable and the meals a decent size.  Some cool 80's music was playing in the background and noise from the TV's in the bar were audible; a pleasurable experience so much better than the typically dead atmospheres of other restaurants I've been in. A hidden gem in San Fransisco. 5 stars.

Got to the bar and had prompt service. Good fish tacos, even with a minor mistake with my “hold the...” request. Probably a bit overpriced, but the atmosphere an Irish pub should have (well, an American urban version).  Excellent bar staff. Worth visiting.
Lovely food and friendly staff. Tucked out of the way, but we'll worth a visit.

Food's pretty good (we got the beef stew and the bangers with beans and mash, both were tasty but served kinda...lukewarm). Beer selection is okay, a bit subpar for what you'd expect at an Irish pub. Decent selection of American, scotch, and Irish whiskies. Good place to sit outside when the weather's nice. Overall, a solid neighborhood pub.
Great food with a traditional Irish Pub atmosphere. Great, quick service as well.

reviews.text: Normally have a great experience at Auntie Anne's locations, but this one was a major disappointment. Not only were they out of the advertised pepperoni pretzel nuggets but they were out of the cheese dipping sauce. The only excuse to running out of one of your major dipping sauces is poor management. It's not like they have to make the cheese sauce. It doesn't even take that much room to store hundreds of the little containers.

I LOVE the Almond pretzel and my son likes the mini dogs. The staff here is really friendly and I usually have to wait like 10 minutes but it is worth it to get a fresh out of the oven pretzel. We usually get the buy 3 get one free, stamp card ready! The drinks are pretty good too so I'm a happy camper.
Love it and staff is very cool. Got a pretzel for free by just telling how much I love their Pretzldogs. Wish I could have them in Germany, too.
We bought the original and the cinnamon bites. Apart from way too much sugar on the bites, they were both very good.
How they make the pretzels taste so good, I will never know. I suspect the secret has to do with butter and sugar.
