reviews.text: Seasonal produce inspires the French dishes. Best to make a reservation (particularly for the lunch crowd, it's a downtown favorite) Cozy atmosphere with lots of wood, marble, brick, and metal details. Staff is attentive and has a nice cocktail menu. Definitely, opt in for the dessert options. They're always delicious.

An amazing experience at this place. Monica and Arnie were our bartenders and really took care of us! Monica had a lot of great recommendations. Nelson was very friendly too and took care of us when the bartenders were busy! Definitely a great experience. Grab a Manhattan while you're there....you wont regret it!

It's a quaint restaurant that's dark, cozy, and intimate.  The music playing was an extra.  I ordered the Tom Collins and Lobster fries.  The drink definitely hit the spot and the Lobster Fries were delicious.  A must when in the Financial district!  Didn't hurt my pockets either.

Ammmaaazing food. Everyone was talking about what they got. I had the roasted chicken breast which was cooked very well and juicy. My friend next to me got the Sole Fillet and that tasted even better haha. The interior was definitely an eclectic mix of styles that somehow seem to mesh together.

Only complaint was unfortunately my waitress. Super kind and friendly but she was not very attentive. Aka she poured more water in my cocktail before I could say nooooo. Took a while to come back and check on us. I'm assuming because they we're busy.
Best bar and staff in the area. Not so loud you can't hear yourself

reviews.text: Absolutely beautiful restaurant and pleasant atmosphere. The vibrancy is all around as you walk in...the colors, the service, the food, the drinks, the music. The food was delicious and filling. Bartender was very engaging and provided good drink recommendations. A place worth checking out for the full experience.

Second time in a year we've come from Boise, Idaho and had the pleasure. Just being in their vibe makes me happy! Food and staff are superb. Had the chance to take our 16 year old, she adored it and the experience. Thank you and be back soon! Danny, Boise ID

I went here for the first time with my friend. Restaurant looks really good from outside and it feels more simple when you get in. It is dark inside and you may think that its romantic bit it's really not because tables for two are next to each other. So literally you can hear what you neighbors are talking about. The food was really tasty and good. But its sooo over priced!

I like to come here often because it is very difficult to find a Indian restaurant in bay area with clean and decent environment. Their food quality is very good as well. They also a complete bar which is an add on. They are good with South Indian dishes I would not recommend any north Indian items here...

Great food with a lot of spices and fantastic flavor. Took one star out to reflect the dark ambiance, aka, need flashlight to read menu and see the food. I think it should be called a blind taste restaurant. A really good one.

reviews.text: I recently revised my 3 🌟 rating to a 4 🌟 rating, as the customer service, quality of food, and cleanliness have all improved as of late. I'm sure there have been several new employees, and the senior staff have stepped up their game, considerably. Still, there's room for improvement, but all-in-all this is becoming a decent place for a meal at any time of the day 😊

For this one particular Subway - it was better when the last girl was working here. But I don't think she works here no mo.
The last five occasions on visiting this franchise, the veggie add ons were quite skimpy, even when ordering a "normal" Veggie sub you would think they would pile it on since the vegetable garnishes  are the main ingredients. 
It is possible that this is one of those franchises that protested bringing back the $4.99 foot long. So in order to economize losses, all the regular menu  items have to be "sub" standard.

I think this most recent visit will be my last visit to this particular Subway.

Btw, there are now 3, count them three Subway franchises in the Fisherman's  wharf area,  one of these things doesn't belong. Because they have a bad habit of cross contamination of the condiment bottles. By not thoroughly cleaning the bottles. And that same place hasn't restocked the CO2 for the soda fountain  - their Coke, Dr Pepper Sprite all carbonated beverages are flat or quite weak, meaning they taste like coloured water, but not soda.
Very quick service, sandwich of the day. Man I was hungry, delicious.
Quick sandwichs

It's an intimate place to eat and never busy. The counter intelligence is helpful without being gratuitously pushy to buy chips or a soda with a sandwich. The only drawback is the homeless people who come inside, rummage through the uneaten food inside the store. It was very off-putting.

reviews.text:
The food was good. The wait was absurd. I came here with my boyfriend for my birthday. We had a reservation and were seated immediately upon arrival. We put in drink orders and appetizer and entree orders shortly thereafter. The drinks came in a reasonable amount of time, as did the apps. We waited an hour and 45 minutes for entrees. The waiter stopped by several times to apologize and let us know the food would be ready soon, but that turned out to not be true. Nothing was comped for the long wait either. The food was good, but not good enough to wait at the table for nearly two hours.

Highlights were the coconut rice and the cocktails.

One of the best places San Francisco has to offer!  My friend and I ordered the Chef's sampler for appetizers, which included two different rolls, dumplings, tuna and pork ribs, all of them were very good, each with a special flavor. For main we had the lamb ribs and a side of fried rice; the lamb was so soft and the flavours were amazing! Finally we had the layer crepe cake, a bit sweet but with an espresso you have the perfect combination. Definitely a place that I would recommend and would love to visit again!
Great place . It had a nice vibe. Good food. The restaurant is always full. The lounge upstairs is nice and relaxing. Not too crowded. Awesome personnel. Love to coming back to the place.

The name of this place hides the delicious Vietnamese haute cuisine offerings Le Colonial is known for.  First class service, excellent, creatively prepared food, wine tasting, all wrapped up in what must have been the drawing room of a San Francisco men's club at one time.  Don't let the decor deceive. Le Colonial is a great place to eat!

Came here for a team dinner with my company. Michelle made it easy to organize and order for everyone, while be conscious of dietary restrictions. The food was delicious and the drinks were strong and tasty! Be aware: they have a dress code here!

reviews.text: Best pizza place ever. They have fire oven baked thin crust pizzas, fresh toppings and delicious cocktails. Me and my friends love to come here. The location is so beautiful. Sit outside and enjoy the beautiful view of the water and the bay bridge. Good place for brunch/dinner
Great experience! Staff know how to earn tips. Great work Palomino. Would definitely recommend going here. Atmosphere, food & drinks... 5 star. Shout out for Jim. H for looking after us.

The food was pretty good but service was sub par.  If you had to rate this restaurant by food and atmosphere alone I think it'd receive a 4/5 star rating. However, when our group ordered drinks, the drinks came extremely late, the servers missed some people, and we had to keep reminding servers about our drinks.  Overall though the atmosphere is really nice and good food.

I came here for lunch on a weekday with a large group of about 10 or so people. We made a reservation the morning of but it also wasn't very busy. There's a great view of the Bay bridge which you can see from their outdoor seating and some tables inside. There is a wide variety of choices on the menu so this was a perfect place to bring a large group.  We were celebrating 2 birthdays and my engagement so they brought out 3 creme brulees which  we all shared and everyone enjoyed very much!
Drinks are delicious and their happy hour is from 3 to close. So the perfect place to sit and chat as you watch the sunset. Also the gorgonzola fries are to die for. A definite must get.

reviews.text: Wow amazing food...the beef dumplings are the best...unique since dumplings are usually pork or shrimp...the sushi was great high quality ingredients...the best California roll ever! But the desert the warm chocolate with ice cream was to die for! Really recommend this restaurant it's worth the price.  Didn't try the meat but can only imagine how good it must be. Finally one of the best service I have seen... food immediately removed when done from the table the waiter attentive to every last detail. Will definitely try this at other locations.

The food and service was superb.
Erik and Tina took really great care of us. The chefs are artists as well as chefs. They have some great vegetable dishes as well the lamb was amazing. Perfectly cooked. 
The sake and wine was very good.
It is best to make a reservation as it is very popular.
The restrooms are spotlessly clean.
The restaurant manager Lelani is one of the most conscientious people in the world. Committed to excellent service.
The sushi is of the highest quality.

Came here for the $65 restaurant week special in January. For the money, the restaurant week menu was worth it. Based on food alone, this isn’t the best place for sushi and isn’t the best place for steak, but if you should require both in one restaurant then this is probably your best bet. Prepare to spend $$$$ if you’re not coming during restaurant week. Also your clothes can somewhat stink after dinner because they have an open air kitchen.

A good place to eat sushi! Honestly, my first Telltale sign of a sushi restaurant is if I smell fish. If my Sushi smells fishy then I think it's old and I won't eat it. This place had fresh sushi and the ambience was quite nice as well!

Great sushi spot in the financial district. The employees are very friendly and good at their job. i like to sit at the sushi bar so i can watch Taku prepare my food. Total pro. The bar downstairs is pretty sweet too. Pop over to Kels next door for drinks afterwards.

reviews.text:
I had not been to Bottom of the Hill in years until last night 2/1/18. 
The Lillingtons were in town and I did not want to miss out on this! 
Doors at 8:30, show at 9. I arrived at 9:10 and the place was already packed. 
Friendly staff checking ID's and tickets. I did not order food or beverage while there, but saw others enjoying spirits and eats.
It gets pretty warm inside, but there's a back patio you can escape to. 
Clean, stocked restroom.

Attended another (sold out) show on 2/17/18, my car was broken into.  
While they do post notices on their door and windows stating to leave nothing in your vehicle, my car and several others were hit sometime between 9pm -1 am. This venue does not allow in and out privileges for patrons.  With that being said, perhaps they will consider posting security OUTSIDE the venue to deter things like this from happening.  People will be less excited about coming to a venue when their vehicle is likely to get vandalized or worse.  Luckily, there was nothing in my car to steal, however the damage they did to the vehicle itself is costly.  

If you have a hatchback, I recommend removing your rear deck lid so thieves can see you have nothing back there.  Hopefully it saves you a broken window, or worse.
Great venue and staff. The most interesting performance bookings. Food was good, drinks were good. Atmosphere was great.

What a sick venue. Has a good bar with affordable beers for SF, and the window at the back of the stage is neat. It's a pretty small place, and the bands / performers there came out into the venue to hang out and sell merch before and after each set.
Went to a concert here. The venue is pretty nice, but the bathrooms were discusting and the whole placd smelled like cigarettes
Intimate yet lively venue with a cozy backroom and a cute secret courtyard (actually not so secret, as there is a window behind the stage looking out to it...more like hidden in plain sight)

I hear many people complain  how expensive on their bills not knowing the prices and ended paying it.  

  But over all great service and the dining  environment. I would come back again 

Recommended to reserve the table.

Pretty good Dim Sum. Efficient and friendly service elevates the classic dim sum fare, while the occasional modern versions provide the memorable highlights. Points for their table side Peking Duck, it's not something you typically see at Dim Sum houses. Tight seating, cart service, and Quality teas add to the authenticity of the dinning experience.

We were recommended to this place as a must try I'm torn between giving it a one or a two there was only 2 dishes that were average most dishes were below average and one looked inedible and half the dishes were room temperature or cold and considering how much it costs for an average at best dim sum also with below average service I'd never go back or reccomend it... the only 2 dishes I'd recommend was there pot stickers and there duck

Excellent dim sum but overpriced for what you get. The soup dumplings and shiitake were exceptional (5/5), and the other dishes were solid (4/5). We paid $45/person for brunch without drinks. If the venue had $$$ or $$$$ on Google maps’ profile instead of $$, I would rate 4 stars.
Some of the best dim sum in SF. Always a lively crowd so make sure to come hungry but not starving, you might wait a bit.

reviews.text: Great little punk bar that occasionally plays some good metal music as well. Friendly staff (hi Joe at the door!) and killer Bloody Mary's. And the burgers and grilled cheese sandwiches are great too. There's a beer garden space out back, a pool table in the room where you order food and lots of good local beer to order. But remember, they're CASH ONLY so hit an ATM on the way over.

Zeitgeist is an interesting punk/metal bar with a great draft beer selection, decent food, and plenty of outdoor space to enjoy the weather. Definitely a place to end the night, but don't cause a scene. They have a reputation for kicking annoying customers out!

SF institution. Punk vibe and great backyard. When they fire up the q' make sure you get some. One of the top bloody's in the city, great mix and well dressed. Always a fan of Zeitgeist!

PS - CASH ONLY

Many of my friends won't go here anymore because it is too busy but if you ever come on an off time it's such a great hang out spot with great music. I came on a weekday around 4pm and got my veggie burger and Roy Rogers right away. Love the outside patio.

Definitely check this place out if you're in the area.

reviews.text:
It’s a nice, well lit restaurant with a nice ambiance to it. The starting chips are excellent, though the salsa is a bit thin. Service to start is fast, and chips and drinks are refilled quickly. You also get a tall decanter of chilled water at seated tables. 

As for the food: the meats we had were excellent. Vegetables were alright. The tortillas we found were very dry and floury, which took away a lot of the flavor. 

The menu is well labeled for gluten free options and there does not seem to be cross contamination in marked foods (though there is no flag or different plate color for gluten free orders). If this review is updated within 24hrs then you will know the food is not celiac safe!

It’s rather pricey to dine here for the quality of food. Not a bad option, but would not be my first pick.

Everything on the menu is delicious! Love the guacamole that is prepared fresh at the table. Nice tequila selection. Comfortable seats. Has a nice patio that gets sunshine earlier in the day. Great spot for lunch or dinner and happy hour too.
Amazing upscale Mexican. I still like taco trucks on the flipside. But some very creative, flavorful and colorful dishes. Great place. A tad pricey but worth the experience.

The food was good, but perhaps a little upscale or authentic for my tastes. I think I'm so used to super greasy and cheesy Mexican food that anything that's NOT that is too different for me. The food here was fresher, cleaner, and a little under-seasoned. I wanted more "oomph".

Also, the service, while professional and attentive, was slow, and I think this had to do with the food more than anything. Don't expect a quick meal here.
Good food but pricey. Entrees were cold when we finally got them.  Very busy with holiday lunch parties so service was very slow. I love the ambiance. Decor is festive and elegant. Staff were nice.

Though pricy, the ambience, quality of service and availability of valet services make up for it.  The food?  Top notch, high grade and aesthetically pleasing.  Might I add that the bathrooms are in pristine condition.

reviews.text: First time at the Mikkeller bar and it was a weekend. They started serving Brunch recently and if you get a chance try the corn beef and hash. This is no store bought corn beef and it was fantastic.  It went well with the solid beer selection.  My only gripe is the price of the beers. They do have a good amount of one off and unique beers but the price tends to be a bit higher than most places.

A modern twist on a traditional German beer hall with an overwhelming choice of flavourful beers to choose from. The bratwurst is moist and delicious served with plentiful mustard and sauerkraut. Cheerful casual waiters make sure your glass never goes empty and share their knowledge liberally.

Superb atmosphere, a very nice restaurant. Eat at the majestic bar, wonderful. I tasted the pepper steak: really amazing! Some really good bites, lot of good drinks. I will go there for lunch, for after work and drinks, but maybe not for dinner (noisy, full)
But indeed, a very good address

Great beer selection. Tasty food. Did I mention the variety of beers on tap?  And not just a bunch of crappy beer but amazing beers served properly. This is a beer lovers bar. Yes the neighborhood is still a little sketchy but that makes this place legit.

One of the best bars I've been to in SF. The beer choice is very wide and changes often. The food is really nice too. Gets a bit noisy at certain hours but with voices of people talking, definitely not loud music. I loved visiting this place at odd hours, sit at the bar and have conversations with strangers.

reviews.text: Went here for brunch and ordered the sassy bacon and smoked salmon omelet, both were incredible. The bacon is super thick, sweet and spicy, a must-try for bacon lovers. Then there was the omelet which was loaded to the max with quality smoked salmon. There was also the bottomless mimosas with a ton of different juice flavors, which I didn't go that route but they looked good. The venue itself isn't all that attractive, certainly not for brunch, but the tasty menu items and lively vibe make up for it.

Great music, food was delicious and the bottomless mimosas were everything. 
I had the smoked salmon omelet which came with a side salad and potatoes. More than generous sized plate for one. Definitely could have split it with someone and been fine. 
The music was lit (trap rap most of the time I was there which was perfect for the turn up).
Went with a large group so definitely recommend getting reservations of that is the case.
Don't go to bars too often but this place was cool. They could tone it down on the cleaner like anonia cause it was really strong. Most people can't notice cause their getting drunk

Also if you like bringing the club to brunch and not being able to hear and talk to any of your friends while eating, this is the bumpin' place for you.

Best place ever! We're from southern California and my group and I were recommended this place! So fuu, so lively, and our waitress Ashley absolutely amazing!!! So honestly, she knew menus suggestions, and she knew great drinks!!!

reviews.text:
Ate here whilst staying in San Francisco but very disappointed. As a big fan of steaks, I've tried many across the years, in many restaurants in different countries and in all honesty I've had a lot better for a lot less money!!

Very, very overpriced. Why? Dimly lit restaurant that makes it very hard to read menus. Steak was very dry which was a shame as it was a good cut, just badly cooked that rendered it devoid of all succulence. Then they only allow you to share potato and side dishes which may work out well for a number of you but when there's only two people and you don't like or want the same choices it bumps the price up to actually have what you want. They refused to do half potato half veg option! Why?? They're cooking the stuff anyway- a good restaurant would allow you to do that!! Had to order a share portion side of potatoes and veg which wasted a lot and everything was way too salty!! Adding salt to everything does not make it better! Cooking it to retain its natural flavours makes it good. I actually felt guilty afterwards for wasting so much money (over 200 dollars on one main for two people) for a distinctly average chain store steak. Won't be visiting again
Wonderful food and atmosphere.  Reservations are a must!  Service was outstanding.  Be prepared to pay out some $$$$$$.  WELL WORTH IT.
Good food and good service. One thing that is the downside is one of their neighboring businesses RocksBox. Yeah they suck.

Highly overpriced (even by NY standards).  While the steak was good, they do not know how to cook it.  There was no crust or char on the outside.  I looked at the kitchen (it is an open air kitchen) and see they cook the steaks (as well as other food at the same time) in a broiler which is about 12" under the flame.    Not the way to do it.  If you want a good steak, there is only one place -  Peter Luger's in NY.  There are other steak houses in San Francisco which offer a better steak.  This was a huge disappointment.

The perfect storm. Great food and great service on the bar at this classy food and bar restaurant. Was there twice in the week, eating a few of the bar menu, reasonably priced and cooked to perfection, both the set of 3 steak fillers or the trip of burger sliders

reviews.text: Nice fish restaurant in down-town San Francisco, hidden in a little side street. For a good table discussion probably too noisy but you can also sit at the bar and eat. Worth a visit...

A good seafood (mostly) spot in an off the main Street location. The place has high ceilings and is airy, which makes you almost feel like you're in a fish market. The wine pairings are suited for fish (white or rose) and go nicely with the food offerings. Mussels, chowder, oysters are all solid. Recommend for those who don't want to go to fisherman's wharf for some good seafood.
Food and drinks were great but it was a little pricey for the appetizers. Good spot for a happy hour

I have been here many times and usually the experience has been fantastic. This time was terrible. Our server "Casper" was one of the worst servers I've ever had in my entire history of dinning out. She was terrible. Our large party (7 people) was treated poorly. Food was tasty as always but the service experience was bad enough for me to write this review. Sorry to see such an excellent restaurant ruined by such a terrible service experience....avoid until they correct the staff issue.

Delicious meat for days. They keep coming back with different options (including shrimp) unless you say you're good. In addition to that, they have a great salad bar. You will not leave hungry. I'm not an expert  but the wine selection seemed ok and they had beer and mixed drinks.

Plan to eat for hours.  When I go here I plan ahead and eat as little as I can for a day or so before I go. This is a marathon; not a sprint.  Take your time and set a pace you can maintain or you will miss out..... and or die from eating too fast.

reviews.text:
We were immediately seated for our reservation and the service was good. 

We ate absolutely everything, practically licking the plates clean. It was delicious and the perfect amount of food. We shared the bacon bread and green salad and then each got an entree. The pork chop is breaded, which was unexpected but delicious. 

Very cozy place. The interior is very similar to Tunnel Top, which is next door.

Excellent bit of France in SF. Great service, had our own mini wine tasting when choosing the red to go with our steaks. The wine list has an excellent choice of reasonably prices wines. The tuna starter and the steaks were cooked perfectly and everything was well presented and very tasty.  Atmosphere on cozy top floor dining area just perfect for a romantic evening. An excellent night out, wouldn't hesitate to recommend.

Delicieux. Feels like you’ve discovered a little bistro in Paris. Dark, moody lighting with seats at the bar, main seating upstairs. Reservations are definitely recommended. Service is great and the food is outstanding! I had the salmon which was medium rare with perfectly crispy salmon. We also ordered the crispy brussel sprouts (amazing), lamb appetizer (succulent). My boyfriend had the bistro steak and loved it. The only reasons I’m not giving 5 stars is the menu is a little limited, and it’s a bit pricey. That being said, everything they make is perfectly executed, and I love bringing friends here for special occasions.

I've dined here twice and it was excellent both times. They were very accommodating with regards to our theater reservations and made sure we were able to fit in dessert. I really like the wine recommendations from the wait staff, can't wait to go back!
Excellent French food. Funky, casual, cool atmosphere.  Definitely recommend.

reviews.text:
Simply put, we loved this place. Perfect for a lazy sunny afternoon lunch and beer.

We sat out the back on the terrace, over looking the water. I had the Longshoreman's Special (American sized Chowder I was informed) and the wife had the Crab and Shrimp Louie Salad. Both were tasty, good, hearty meals. They had a good and varied  selection of beverages, but what really stood out were the serving staff. I believe it was Tony who served us predominately, but they were all lovely. He noticed I had almost finished my beer, and offered to have one ready and waiting in 5 minutes for me. Perfect.

As an afternoon retreat away for the hustle and bustle of the main town it is a great choice and for me that's why it gets a 5. 

One question though. What is the deal with that heater?!?!

Warning - Our credit card information was stolen from this restaurant. 

Shortly after we left this restaurant we were contacted by the credit card company and notified about suspicious purchases. This card hadn't been used for any other purchases for weeks before and nothing after. I called the restaurant and was promised a call back...that was months ago and I'm still waiting.

Otherwise the food is just "okay". 3 stars at best.

They have a small selection of beers on tap, the service at the bar is a bit slow but friendly! If you come during happy hour you will catch the live music and great deals too! Also on the first Thursday of the month they have a Ducati bike night! Highly recommend that day and around 6 pm!
What a wonderful place for a brunch. Right by the water or inside, as u may please. Cocktails on point and breakfast menu to kill for. Brilliant place for nice relaxed sunny winter mornings...

An old San Francisco staple that never disappoints. The food is delicious, the bar tenders are very friendly and knowledgeable, the view is nothing to scoff at, and the art on the walls is entertaining. Word of advice: be kind to staff and patrons, don't be a jackass, and have a good time. Pretty sure the kitchen staff are wizards, because the food was freaking tasty!

result.formatted_address: 599 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
result.name: Honey Honey Cafe & Crepery

reviews.text: Good food but expensive.  A full breakfast with OJ and coffee costs $20.  I was a tourist needing breakfast in downtown San Francisco, and there seemed to be very few choices within walking distance of Union Square.  I tried Honey Honey and ordered the 2+2+2 platter -- 2 eggs, 2 pancakes, 2 slices of bacon.  The orange juice ($5 extra) was fresh-squeezed on the spot, and was delicious, but it was served at room temperature, not chilled.  I was satisfied with the breakfast, very tasty, but wanted to give a note of caution about the prices.

There was a huge queue to get in, then another queue to order. Overall it must have taken 45 minutes to order. I am not sure if this is because it was a holiday, or if it is like this every weekend.

There is a good selection of vegetarian options, although too much avocado for my liking. Still it wasn't hard to find something to my liking.

When the food arrived it was tasty, although a bit on the cold side. I might have gone for some dessert, but that would mean queuing up again. You have to know what you will want when you first order.

Big menu, and pretty affordable. Order at the counter and they will serve you your food. I didn’t get an option for a side with my sandwich. I got a California sandwich and an almond cookie for around $12. Decent service and decent atmosphere. If I lived closer it would be a place to go when I couldn’t decide.

Had the honey honey cake with some coffee which was very yummy but make sure you like really sweet food. Both the sweet and savory crepes are great. The service is quick and the servers and bussers are nice and efficient and helped us get a table once we were at the counter ordering.

This place is so good and they have a nice selection for breakfast. Lots of choices, but you can definitely find something good. Eggs are stove of the best. Crepes are excellent. Staff is very helpful and very cool looking atmosphere.

result.formatted_address: 490 Pacific Ave, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
result.name: Cotogna

reviews.text:
Hands down a favorite in SF. Nestled in the heart of Jackson Square's design district, this chic restaurant begs for your time. The service is always impeccable and the food - out of this world. Every time, I want to try each item on the menu, but never have enough time, nor the appetite to handle such a daunting task.  The ambiance is beautiful at any time of the day with seating options to suit anyone's fancy.  I'd like to meet ONE person that doesn't like Italian food and show them Cotogna.

Go watch the chefs in action through the window from outside and they'll have to ask you to leave since you'll be fogging up the glass with your tongue hanging out and breath on the window. Trust me - you're jaw will drop with every bite. I say, let it hang!

My husband and I had the ravioli with shrimp and their famous pork chop dish. "The pork chop" on the menu was actually  pork belly. A bit fattening.  We had to cut out quite a few of the fatty bits. But the taste is really good. The ravioli on the other hand is absolutely amazing. The shrimp sauce is rich but not overly done. The service is okay. Overall, it is a bit pricey but certainly a great restaurant.

From ambience and decor to the perfectly executed pastas and pizzas, to the detailed attentive service... you can't go wrong. Lunches are just as crowded as dinners so make sure to make a rez in advance.
The best dinner I ate in a long time. Everything was perfect. Try will mushroom pizza you will not regret it.

Unfortunately, none of the staff can make seating a smooth experience. After asking for a seat, we were offered the bar or chef’s counter(great! No problem for a party of 2 :) ) and told to wait 20 min, we were told we’d get a phone call, after an hour of wandering North Beach, no call.. so we walk back, and arrive to to a rude staff, some non-sense about a table being cleared and then obviously we were just walked to barren bar. Bottom line, businesses that lie when they fall short and insult you in front of other customers to save face don’t deserve the investor money that makes their comical existence possible.

result.formatted_address: 256 Pier 39 Concourse, San Francisco, CA 94133, USA
result.name: Hard Rock Cafe

reviews.text:
Had a really bad experience overall. 
Seating was really fast, and it’s a very nice inside which I was grateful for but our waitress....... She talked ONCE the whole time we were here. She asked for our order and my husband gave his order and she walked away and I had to wave at her 3 times so I could order my food.. I ordered some ranch and she spilled it all over the table and walked off. She didn’t ask if we wanted refills, if the food was okay, if we needed anything. Just set our food down and walked away. Didn’t see her again at our table until she brought the check, and she still didn’t speak. I wanted my first time here in SF at the Hard Rock Cafe to be a nice experience but she ruined it for my husband and I. We will not be coming back in the future.

I got to say I was surprised. Reviews were not very good for this place. However they cooked my burger properly. The bartenders worked together and never let our drinks go dry. We forgot out receipt for the limited edition glass and the bartender went right over and to the cashier and took care of us. The only reason I took a star off was the bathroom was a little dirty and smelly.

Came to eat here because a family member recommend it. Overall, horrible service! I waited a total of 1hr & 40mins. The waiters ignored us for 30mins before coming to help us. I asked for some sauce with my order and The waiter that was helping us didn't bring it. I reminded him and he never brought it. I had to ask another waiter and he also couldn't do the simple job. The food was good don't get me wrong but they took too long. I suggest that if you are willing to wait as long as I did then go for it... if not just go somewhere else. Very disappointed of this place. I give it 0 stars not even one.... had to add the star on this because if I don't it won't post. 😝👎
The food was fantastic.  Our waitress was very concerned to get us outstanding service.  Anyone in this area should stop in for good food.

Just had dinner with my fiance and 2 friends on our first night in SF. Overall, the food was the usual for a Hard Rock Cafe anywhere. The service on the other hand was down right disappointing, especially after an outstanding experience at the New York cafe just last week. Drinks didn't get refilled at all during the meal, nor did we get any water for the table. Staff did not take away our plates after we had finished, we sat and continued to chat for close to an hour with dirty plates and empty drinks still sitting there. Nobody seemed to care. Very disappointed and won't be back.

reviews.text: This is an old school concept with servers wearing suits and you're tucked away from other diners in your own big leather booth. Hearty meal with nice pastas, meats (veal is my favorite), salad, and soup options. Decent wine and cocktail menu. Front room is always fun to drop in for a drink and people watch.

One of my favorite spots in San Francisco. Never had a bad meal or bad service. They are consistently good. Several different dining rooms, including a counter, hidden in the back. My favorite place to hang out is in the spacious bar, if I can get a seat by the fireplace. Great, cozy, spot for people watching, having a drink, and the full menu is served as well. Reasonable prices, good food, friendly servers.

The Caesar salad was good. Calamari were good. Hamburger was ok, and Joe’s Special, their signature dish was terrible!  The spinach was bitter, there was hardly any egg and it tasted burnt. I’ve made Joe’s Special at home so much better. Not planning on ever returning.
Love this spot! Great crab Benedict seriously! Original Irish coffee and a great bar! History and local feel mixed with great food and service! Bravo!

Yes.  They serve Italian food.  But I go there for one of the best burgers and fries in town.  LOUD...in a good way.  And remember when restaurants had real PROFESSIONAL waiters?  Well, they work here now.

reviews.text: I just cannot say enough of this place. I must have recommended this restaurant to at least over 50 people. The food is good as any high quality expensive restaurant in San Francisco. But it is so much more affordable. When I am visiting San Francisco this is my go-to place if I want to have something great to eat. This is not a five star restaurant it's a 10 Star restaurant in my opinion. The servers are very nice. And the decor and Ambience is super. Do not miss going to this restaurant if you are in San Francisco. Truthfully Joe

The food is pretty dang good. I like their cause and it seems that they’re seeing results from it. These guys are obviously not seasoned waiters as you do need a level of patience With them. You’ll tend to wait a while on simple things like your drinks getting refilled or the timing of your food coming out. They’re always nice and courteous. I’ve enjoyed my meals from here

This is the best kept non-secret in SF. Everything about this place is fantastic! The setting, right on the Embarcadero; the restaurant itself is very classy while allowing casual attire; the food is expertly prepared, tasty and at a price that makes you think you’re looking at a menu from the 70’s!  And last, but definitely not least is the staff...professional, courteous and very service oriented. The only way you could go wrong with this place is to NOT go there. Breakfast , lunch or dinner you’ll be glad you tried it.

Good quiet atmosphere on a rainy Thursday night. Their hot fudge is delicious and the leg of lamb falls off the bone.  :) Their deep fried mashed potatoes  and marinara were  also  really  good. Very well priced apps and desserts won't break the bank.
Always great. Love this place. Reasonably priced with great ambiance. Recommend it highly.

reviews.text: Hell yeah! This place is great! They serve great food,  like burgers and sushi. They even have delicious desserts such as ice cream sandwiches with cookies made in-house. Please go here. I beg you. If you're on the fence about this place, give it a try. If you don't like it, you need to see a doctor who checks taste buds.

If your'e going in a larger group then you have a better chance of trying out all the burgers. However, if you're going in a small group of two or three people, I suggest to try a slider. A normal sized burger is 6 ounces and costs about $12/$13 while sliders are 3 pieces of 2 ounces each and cost the same $12/$13 but the advantage is you can try more burgers in one go. While there can be one slider, the others can order one burger each. For me and my friend, we did a slider, a normal burger and truffle fries. Must haves - Umami burger and Truffle fries. Happy hour made the truffle fries possible for just $3. Glutton heaven.

Incredibly delicious burgers. This is one of the few places that serves the impossible meat, if no one told me it wasn't meat I would never know the difference, the only way to really tell is to have another burger side by side for comparison. The truffle burger is to die for, if you are a truffle lover, this is burger alone is worth the visit. The place is a bit pricey, I would go back only when im really craving that truffle burger or when I want to take my vegetarian friends to a burger joint.
Burger is solid, bacon is thick and ample but rarely crispy enough to my taste. It's worth trying! Friendly and quick service.
Outstanding! BRAVO!!!  Perfect - FRESH Much positive has been reported and it's all true. I have never had a burger this good.

reviews.text: This place always has fun themed events (mac & cheese day, tater tot day, etc) featuring local food trucks and vendors; always a delicious time when you stop in! I usually skip the bottomless beer since there isn’t quite enough going on to spend a great amount of time, but to each their own!

My favorite truck is the empanadas truck and it is here often! There is also a nice covered eating area that's warm. We love coming here when the weather is nice.

There are restrooms in a temporary building, they are clean-ish, definitely serviceable. All in all it's a nice food truck park with lots of options and absolutely delightful on a sunny day.

Overall I love the variety here and the events they host. Location-wise it can be a little bit rough to find parking (especially if you aren't comfortable parallel parking). I usually come here when it's packed. However, I went last weekend during the day when it was super empty and pigeons had their run of the place -- hopping on tables, chairs, anywhere there could have been scraps. It made me a bit uncomfortable knowing a table I chose to eat at could have recently had been walked all over by birds. I'm unsure how often the tables and chairs are disinfected at Soma StrEat Food Park but something to be aware of.
Loved this place! Super cute and wide food variety. Absolutely a must stop. Will be back here.
This place is super cool, great food and awesome atmosphere. The value isn't the best overall, but that changes truck to truck. Great for a quick bite in San Fran.

reviews.text: Great pizza. Get the deep dish. Good for dining in or take out. It can get busy so if you plan on eating there be prepared to wait for a table.
Love the deep dish with cornmeal crust! It’s not that heavy as the traditional flour dough and it has a very characteristic taste. They are quite fast which is rare for deep dish pizza place.

THIS IS MY FAVORITE DEEP DISH OF ALL TIME! And definitely my favorite pizza in San Francisco.  Great vibes - perfect for a casual date night with a bottle of wine or a night out with a few friends. The Classic Deep Dish is AMAZING.
30 minutes wait for deep dish is well worth it! Not stodgy or greasy, just really great pizza. Good beer and cocktails with friendly service. New favourite pizza in SF

This was an AMAZING PLACE.
First of all it's not a touristy place. It wasn't easy to locate this place from simple view but when we found it, it was worth it. 
It was crowded. But we didn't wait much to get a table. Also noisy but it was a youthful ambiance. Got a few minutes to the waiter to bring us the menus but we were okay. 
Loved everything. We got a Mixed salad which was perfect for 3 persons. And also we got a Italian Combo Deep Dish Pizza. We got to wait a little but but the salad really entertained us. The pizza arrived and it was amazing! The ingredients were fresh and everything tasted super good. The pizza was enough also for 3 persons, we took 2 slices on a box. 
I dunno but I am definitely coming back next time I go to San Francisco because this is hell of a good place to meet locals and have a nice dinner!

reviews.text: Oh my God. The chorizo/fried egg pizza is my jam. Tasty cocktails. Great for lunch on a weekday, when you won't have to wait (long). Wait staff is chill/friendly/very professional. In many ways this place embodies San Francisco for me. Trendy crowd.

Came here for restaurant week so will have to return for their regular menu which I've heard good things about. The cauliflower soup and chicken liver pate were my favorites. The fried chicken po boy was just alright. The brioche bun was dry, the chicken didn't have much flavor and the Cole slaw tasted bitter to me. Friendly service and cute decor they have nice heaters which made the patio area tolerable even on a chilly day.

I love the decor and atmosphere of this place! 

They have an adorable outdoor sitting with heaters in the back of the place as well as in front. 

The food was pretty good, a little on the expensive side, but really tasty stuff that I can justify paying a little more for.

An awesome place for taking a vegetarian friend. Have no fear, there's still some meat dishes on the menu but its healthy, fresh, quick and surprisingly reasonable when it comes to the final bill. Great spot in the Castro.

I took a large group (40) to Starbelly for a corporate dinner - we rented out the back patio. The group had a wonderful time and I got nothing but compliments on the restaurant choice!

The managers and staff made the whole process so easy - they were incredibly accommodating when our group size changed, were very helpful with dietary restrictions, and overall wonderful. The wait staff was professional, quick, easy to work with, and very flexible. 

The food is amazing! Definitely try the pasta with jalapenos and bacon - we asked for the bacon on the side to make it vegetarian-friendly. We ate up every bite of what we were served - there was more than enough food, but it was so tasty we couldn't stop!

Thank you to Starbelly & staff for an awesome night!

EDIT: 

I have since been back on my own dime for dinner and drinks. They have delicious cocktails for only $9 (which is a steal in SF!). The Starbelly pizza is definitely my favorite, along with the burratta toast.

reviews.text: We were an early reservation so the place wasn't full. We were seated on the top level of the restaurant and seated towards the very back of the room with the most lighting, we should've got better seating, especially with a friend who is SF food critic at the table. It wasn't the most elegant part of the restaurant. It took at least 30 minutes to be served a glass of water-basically the ordered drinks came first. The group I came with were sitting there waiting too long for a glass of water. Always offer water before you can get to the real drink list. Sitting there with nothing is never a way to start a "supposed"  fine dining experience. For the most part the dining experience was okay. I ordered their ribeye steak medium rare, I've ordered it this way in many restaurants and have only had one other experience where I could say the temperature of my steak wasn't done right. I was served a very rare steak, however they were very accommodating in taking it back and cooking it a little bit more. Which I never like to do because I never want to offend the chef nor have any chef do anything to my meal. When it came back from the kitchen it was pretty delightful, a little bit more cooked than I would have liked-but very good- compliments of the chef!! Probably the worst experience was going to the bathroom. For what I would call a pretty nice place-I was a little bit thrown off by the bathroom-they could do better, and keep it much cleaner. There were mistakes like my dessert coming with raspberry sauce instead of Carmel, but hey no one is perfect. Roy's is nice, but I'd only go back if someone really wanted to go.

I have been here many times for bothboersonal and business dinners. I have mostly had both stellar experience with the food and the service. On occasion there may be some slower service when very busy but still acceptable. The tomahawk we had was phenomenal, a bit large on portion size but easily shared among a few. Other dishes including sides were equally as good as were the desserts.
Was shocked at how terrible the food was... I went to the one in LA years ago and it was awesome. Bf and I were both super disappointed.
The atmosphere was great , the food was great. The service was outstanding. I had the fish and I don't think I've had fish better ever
Will was an amazing server. Food was great!!!

Overall the dinner is pricey, but you may like to hang out with friends at the bar or courtyard, and enjoy the live piano and cello performance here.
Artichoke heaven. Amazing smoked salmon. Great and fast service... (The fresh, light, hearty  and tasty spinach dip was a mayor plus...even the home made corn chips!)

Overpriced to the extreme and boring omelette (except for the eggshells in it hahaha) but the fries were delicious. The burger was $21 (with fries or coleslaw) but it was decent, although not as good as it used to be. (Not worth $21 of course).  Nice music. Incredible fireplaces though! Nice ambience!  Possibly 3 stars and perhaps my mom and I were just unlucky.

Amazing restaurant!! Spinach artichoke dip was heavenly, barely any cream. Grilled artichokes to die for. Smoked salmon was just a filet of salmon that was smoked in-house, OMG! Organic cider too. And spectacular service!

reviews.text: Love their grilled cheese sandwiches. Sometimes the bread can seem a little dry, but the other ingredients more than make up for it. Always crowded, especially on weekends and holidays. But it is a great place to eat something like pasta, salad or sandwich. It offers several vegetarian options. There is not much place to sit, you have a counter with some benches.
Nice sandwiches, fast and polite service. Bit pricey.

We were only in town for one day, but at least our cruise ship gave up plenty of time - 8a-11p. Plenty of time to explore with our San Fran friends! Fellow elite, Ms. S. is a fan of this place and introduces me to this place. It was a refreshing and easy walk from our cruise port and the perfect place to grab a breakfast sandwich. 

Goat Cheese and Seasonal Jam - Simple and nice. Soft bread and bold flavors. 3/5

Cheesey Bacon Breakfast Sandwich - Amazing! Served on a longer loaf and cut in half - this thing was pretty huge. More importantly, it was absolutely dripping with gooey cheese! Add bacon and things only get better. This was definitely 5/5. 

Blueberry Milk - Pretty straightforward. Blueberry flavored milk. Not overly sweet or thick, it was just right. 3/5

Habit forming - proceed with caution.  If you want to learn about cheese and try before you buy this is a fantastic option.  Tell them what you want to do with it and they will find you the perfect cheese for your taste and application.

reviews.text: This is a good lunch place. The place was busy but they sent us to the public seating area. The food was fantastic. The cheese plate was big and flavorful. The salmon tartare was delicious and the salads were really fresh. A great place, we will definitely come back for lunch again.

I had a great experience here. Service was on point and always one step ahead of me. Food was expertly crafted and flavorful. The dining area can get really loud but it's jovial and inviting. You get the impression people feel relaxed amongst all the noise.

I had the beef duo and jalapeno cornbread, which were both excellent. Tender meat and robust, sharp flavors

This was a solid dinner and I would definitely go again. Most of the dishes were about $30, except for a large, 60 day aged ribeye ($67). Our waiter suggested it would be a good one to share so my wife and I went for it as our main entree.

The rest of the items we ordered were great, but our steak, which we ordered medium rare, was medium well at best. We couldn't taste anything special about it. The waiter finally came by after quite a while and asked how it was. I never send anything back but was very disappointed with the steak and brought up how overcooked it was. He immediately offered a new one and we took him up on it. 

It was a bit of a wait and I felt a bit guilty since we had eaten at least half the other steak, but I'm so glad we did. The second steak was a bit on the rare side, but it was an amazing steak. I've never had a dry age steak with that much flavor (and a bit of funk at times). So, in the end it was a wonderful experience and we loved the steak.
This was one of the best meals I've ever had. While it took my group 30 minutes after our reservation time to get seated, I thought the food was worth it. Definitely try the duck breast.
Inventive menu, well executed. Fresh ingredients creatively prepared. Great urban-contemporary atmosphere. Helpful waitstaff.

reviews.text:
Have never seen such a selection of whiskeys. It's rather pricey but the location is worth it I suppose. I tried 120 proof scotch, don't remember the name but advice to the novice like me - be aware, it's a fire in a glass.

Great place to go with friends or coworkers after work. Prepare to spend some money buy you will enjoy it.

Food is great and booze selection on point. If you're a whiskey lover go here! It's on the water so nice view and decor feels like Hardware Restoration. Fried chicken is amazing and they use cool glassware for all different drinks. Mac n' Cheese is delicious too. Great location for a date. Call ahead if you're coming with a group to have a table reserved.

I haven’t had fried chicken this good since my mother in law stopped making it.  Perfectly fried with a very savory crust.  The biscuit with the pepper jelly was a great accompaniment.

The bar is stocked with the largest whiskey selection I’ve experienced.  Large selection of craft cocktails, and beers if you drinking whiskey is not your thing.  Excellent service to top everything off.

If you are a student of fine rare whiskies and love expertly crafted cocktails, be prepared to being a kid in a grand candy store. Bartender, Brian, was both approachable and scholarly  but its the opportunity to try those bourbons you've only read about that is the star of the show.  I went for a late 2PM "lunch" on a Friday afternoon  (the ample meat/cheese spread was perfect) and I had the staff and bar practically to myself.

A mesmerizing collection of whiskies, from bourbons to American single malts and much more, this place can provide you with the very right kind of poison you prefer. The staff was curious and helpful, had a nice vibe to the place, the crowd was diverse and friendly as well. We didn't get to try the food but it all smelled really good, also seemed hygienic. It's is a must visit if you're visiting San Francisco area and especially if you're a whiskey maniac like me :)

reviews.text: We were in the city for a concert and dropped by here to eat dinner beforehand and we loved it. An older resturant with lots of character. The line was short & quick, the selection was good, pricing was reasonable and the food tasted great. (It's an order at the counter and take your meal to your table kind of place). The staff was friendly and the waitress was very attentive once we sat down with our plates to order our drinks and she was very informative about the beer selection (which there was a lot to choose from). I ordered the corned beef and cabbage with potatoes and it was so delicious and my husband ordered the pastrami dinner with mashed potatoes with gravy and he also enjoyed his meal. We were overall very happy with our experience. We loved the ambiance...  it's a fun place and we will definitely be back again. Only thing to remember is if you go there... have cash because it's a cash-only restaurant but if you do forget, they do have a ATM :-)

Old San Francisco at its best.  All pastrami, corned beef, Turkey, roast beef, ham, chicken made daily on premise.  Recipes not change from 50 years ago.  Sandwich meats are hand carved and large portions for sandwiches and dinner plates.  Reasonably priced (lowest in expensive San Francisco).  Alcohol is also lowest priced in high priced area of San Francisco.  Decor has not changed in 50 years.  Nothing fancy.  Not for your tourist or executive lunch or dinner crowd.

Line was long, we were caught in the lunch time rush. Always good to see a place busy with customers. Took about 20 minutes to reach the front and order. What it lacks in presentation it makes up for in taste. The side sauce got the beef brisket sandwich was tangy and delicious! Note, cash only. Table service for drinks.

This place was sooooo good! The pastrami was cooked to perfection. Simple meals with big flavor. This is a great place to kick back enjoy some down time with friends, family or other. There is a bar that you can sit at or tables and booths. Nice low key atmosphere. I definitely will be back! PS...the pickles are all you can eat.

Dirty and truly unsanitary. Crumbling walls and accessories, way beyond trying to emulate antiques. Posters and other art elements are taped or glued on so poorly that it is worse than a frat house. Artwork with face of person is a hole instead. The low ceiling in dining area that is beneath the second story bathrooms show that a leak had happened from that source. Not really repaired decently or stained to match. No pride of ownership in decor or food quality. Roast beef was ok, but the canned-like green beans were so peppery that there inedible and had no taste of the vegetable. Chili was so overcooked that the beans were mush. Don't bother coming.

reviews.text:
As others have probably mentioned already, their bread bowl clam chowder is a must try! It is one of the best if not the best clam chowder I've tried so far! I would highly recommend it if you're in the bay area (:

Also, it is very packed so prepared to walk around looking for seats. Consider it as part of the experience.

I really loved this place. The bread animals we bought were so cute. They gave us a tour of the place, and it was amazing. I love the history behind the Boudin sourdough tradition. They have a nice seating selection (inside and out) for us to enjoy. They also have a nice lunch selection (with alcohol should you choose) and a gift shop area as well. It's really an amazing place to eat and relax.

Great place to watch how sourdough bread is made and taste.  Has both indoor and outdoor seating. You must try the clam chowder in the sourdough bread bowl. The sourdough bread here is chewy with a crunchy, crusty crust. 

Always busy. You will have to wait in line to order and wait to pick up downstairs (full service restaurant is upstairs). Service is fast and you will get your meal quick. You can also just buy bread. 

There is a Peet's Coffee within the cafe downstairs if you need your caffeine fix. 

There is a self-guided Boudin museum tour if you are interested about the whole sourdough bread making process and the company's rich San Francisco history.

It's good there is not one near my house because I would be there every day. The bread is so delicious, my husband and i had just that for lunch today. The smell hits you as you walk in and it gets better from there. We bought bread shaped like a Christmas tree from the store and the tree part pulls apart in perfect little rolls. I also had a bread bowl of Clam chowder last night for dinner and it was delicious too.
Great place, great food. Can tour and watch them make that fabulous bread. Can sit down and eat. Good prices, friendly service. The lines are long but the line moves fast

One of the best places in town to get a good German beer. $8 per liter. 

Food is great. Lively place that gets pretty loud but it's all part of the experience.

Solid German food. consistent over the last 10 years? I've been going here. Great German beer selection, and a substantial brunch. It's no nonsense eating here. Tables are communal, and casual is the vibe.

reviews.text:
Bix was great!! We loved the vibe the moment we walked in (it turned out it was originally a bank back when it was first built). The food was AMAZING. I had the duck and it basically melted in my mouth. The vegetables were some of the best I've ever had and it was presented perfectly.
Overall it was one of the best dinning experiences I've had San Francisco!

Very nice atmosphere and really great food. The staff was professional and knowledgeable. The place has a somber quiet mood in the dining area which check is perfect for a date night. Downstairs there is more of a lounge atmosphere. Best poached eggs I have ever had.
Upscale and classy. Steak tartar was incredible. Drinks are great. Dessert was first rate. Great service.

Loved the place! With a strong 30's ambiance this place is wonderful for a good dinner with your colleagues as well as friends. The menu offers all time European-American classics and delicious deserts (must have) that you can enjoy with live music. Will definitely go back!

Great old school Jazz Supper Bar. Can be loud and crowded when offices let out. Excellent cocktails. Bartenders and staff in penguin suits like in times long past. Live jazz nightly. Great food. Some of the best steak tartare in town made tableside  It's a good old standby for a good times with friends after work or even for a special occasion. Make reservations for dinner. I've come since they opened and have never been disappointed.

reviews.text: I had the opportunity to dine at Quince this week, and my review is mixed.  The atmosphere and service were phenomenal, and our group had a wonderful time there.  That said, I have had some of the best meals of my life in places with zero atmosphere and service.  For me, it's all about the food, so here's my analysis of the food at Quince.  It all tasted wonderful and was cooked perfectly, but it over relied on two components that blunted the full force of the dishes, namely truffles and butter.  Nearly every dish in our set course had truffles on it and was drowning in butter, which ended up dulling the cooking rather than allowing it to shine.  I wish the chefs, who are obviously quite capable, were more committed to clean, honest flavors, especially with their earthy Italian cooking.  That got me thinking about why the need for obvious decadence in every dish, and I can only guess that they're catering to the current, moneyed SF crowd.  Make of it what you will.
I love this place. The staff is friendly and helpful. They have great food. The food just melts in your mouth. It is a great place to eat!

The good news and not so good news!
The food was refined and excellent. The atmosphere was a bit pretentious....too much. (Note: we have experienced many comparably rated restaurants) 

The chef's preparation in the kitchen was special.

But the service was incredibly slow. There was a very large party that arrived as we did. However this caliber restaurant should have been able to handle it MUCH better.

We decided to finish our Cali tour with Quince. Starting from calling and making a reservation was the best customer service. We needed to catch a flight after dinner so they accommodated our luggage. Then when we started our dinner, this place was out of this world. The food is so good I can't explain everything because it will ruin the experience. Having the unknown is what truly makes it worth it. Going into the restaurant knowing that your going to be taken care of and enjoy every moment of it. I highly recommend for going for a special occasion, going to try probably the best Michelin star(s) restaurants and you will need to come here once in your life. The authenticity of the food and preparation of the cutlery and plates, to bringing our luggage into our Uber driver, is just a glimpse of what is to be expected. Highly recommend it!

Great service, presentation, and preparation. The wines are ridiculously overpriced but they do have an impressive selection of vintages of the popularly known French Bordeauxs and Burgundys. The place to go if you need to compare a 1982  Chateau Latour with the 1999 - as long as you have the requisite $10,000 to drop on the wine tab. The selection of sub $200 bottles is disappointingly thin.

reviews.text: It was late, I had missed dinner, I was in the neighborhood. I eat a lot of Japanese food as comfort food - Ryoko's knows what they're doing with the traditional items and isn't afraid of putting a twist on some others. Fast, friendly, upbeat vibe. You won't waste your time here.

Food was decent, but the liveliness makes it a five star. The food is relatively good for it's price, but don't come here if you're looking for a fancy Japanese meal. It's more of an izakaya vibe with small dishes and rolls and alcohol. Would definitely come back for a chill night to just drink and chat with friends.

So fun! Friend recommended this place and it didn't disappoint. Food was really solid and the staff were great. Energy in the place was exceptionally high from the moment I walked in to the moment I left. I'll be back for sure. 
Removed one star as the bathrooms are really sketchy. Highly recommend an upgrade.

Decor: 3/5
-Loud yelling, which I understand is the culture however it was a bit too much while trying to enjoy dinner

Service: 4/5
-sign the clipboard for the waiting this as Ryoko's fills up fast
-the food comes as it is prepared though it didn't take terribly long to get our food
-you can split checks into multiple credit cards

Food: 4/5
-Fried baby octopus was my absolute favorite. The flavor was just mouth-watering addicting. I would highly recommend ordering two. Solid 5 out of 5.
-Whole soft shell crab needs some work. If they used the same batter as the fried octopus for the soft shell crab, that would be a winner. 2 out of 5.
-Alcatraz (bbq eel with avocado) and Sexy (crab with salmon and melted cheese) were both on point and a solid 4 out of 5.

Only very rarely do you find a place where the food is as good as the atmosphere. Ryoko's will provide both so it's no surprise that there's always a line of eager foodies blocking the entrance. Inside the air is thick with electro beats, vivacious chatter and laughter. Beer and sake flow freely together with the good times you'll experience during your dinner. 

Not for the people hard of hearing or those expecting a quiet intimate dinner. You come here to eat, drink and share.

reviews.text: Went there for thanks giving and the food was really good. I was not expecting nice food since it is a hotel restaurant and it was thanks giving.  But I was nicely surprised. It was night when I went there but the view is great.  The location is just next to the bay bridge.  There is a huge outdoor area. When the food came, my dished was mixed up with a similar dish that had tons of dairy. I ate half of it until I noticed him looking at me funny. 

Only after I asked.did he tell me they mixed up our plates. I then waited 20 minutes for a proper dish at which point everyone else was done. Barely even an apology. Will not go back ever. Over priced for this bad of service. I feel terrible after eating all that dairy.
Great for happy hour - they have specials til 600pm. A bit swanky and very large - would be good for groups.

This is an Italian restaurant. The menu is short, and the food is delicious. I had the shrimp risotto. The decoration of the restaurant is superb, very modern with frames on the ceiling. The staff is fast.
Good spot across from Ferry building with outdoor dining area. Food was quite tasty and fresh.

reviews.text:
Unfortunately, I did not have a pleasant experience here. I didn't care for the three dishes we ordered. The description looked great in the menu. But when the food arrived, the flavor was quiet bland, and lacking, especially considering the price. If we wanted to ask for anything additional that are standard at other restaurants, they would charge. We ended up leaving unsatisfied with a hefty check.

And the staff was not very friendly. Our server was nice and prompt, kudos. But some of the other staff looked like they didn't want to work there. And the hostess standing outside was rude when we asked a question about the area.

One thing I liked was the garbanzo beans they offered in the beginning. It was the one bright light of the meal.

Such a Great place! We've been coming in for many years, never misses a beat. The food is as great as I remember from my first time here.The service is remarkable.  I can't think of another place where everyone is so happy and pleasant. What an amazing environment!! 
A big thank you to everyone at Nopalito!!!

I love love love this restaurant. The ingredients are fresh, the service is attentive, and the drinks are strong. The salad with the citrus dressing is amazingly light, flavorful, and fresh. reviews.text:
I really enjoy the food here. Had several different dishes here in the past and was always impressed with both quality and presentation. I have only visited this place for lunch so can't speak for dinner or any other times. 

Sraff is very pleasant always. They attended to us just the right number of times and addressed all questions and requests.

I was torn between 4 and 5 stars because of 2 reasons: the prices are on the higher end but I guess location has a lot to do with it and the second - the place is too loud to have a business lunch meeting. I still settled on 5 stars as I believe it is of no fault of the restaurant and cannot be easily addressed.

I highly recommend this place for casual lunch with friends or coworkers.

Pretty standard Thai restaurant fare, well presented in a slightly-trendy-but-not-pretentious setting. Osha is one of my top choices when I'm in the area and just want a reliably good meal in a chilled out environment. Staff are pleasant, service is relaxed but not overly slow.

I enjoyed my Pad Thai noodles but I've had better.  The noodles stuck together and were in a lump.  I forgot to take a picture of the dish.  The service was fine.  It was quite busy on a Friday night on a holiday weekend.  There is a lounge but it is only open Mon-Friday.  There is a bar here.  Unfortunately, the space is small so it felt like it there was too much furniture along with the bar.

Fun atmosphere, classic dishes with a few twists. We had the shrimp spring rolls, wontons, and pumpkin chicken curry. The rice noodle around the rolls was great, the wontons hit the spot with the sweet/spicy sauce. Th pumpkin curry had just the right amount of kick. Service was a little sparse and prices were just a little too high, but you pay a little for the atmosphere I guess. Would give a 3.5 if I could. Solid Thai place that is fun if you want to mix it up a bit.

Good food but service during peak lunch hours isn't great. Be prepared for waiting forever for your food.
If you're selecting this venue for dinner, be careful about the closing time. Google maps says that it closes at 9:30 while this place actually closes at 9.

reviews.text: First location of Mission Chinese! I headed here for a late dinner around 10pm and still had to wait a good 20 minutes or so. It's located in the Mission in a bit of a dodgy area but close enough to the BART so it's not that bad. After getting a table, we ordered the salt cod fried rice and the lamb noodles. The noodles were pretty good- spicy and flavorful. But our salt cod fries rice never came. I had to remind the waitress after a half hour wait. The service overall was very poor as it was hard to get the waiters' attention. Also, you have to step through the kitchen to get to the bathroom which definitely turned me off as I got a view of the cleanliness. It irked me a bit and made me question the sanitary level. Overall food was good but I don't think it was any outstanding Chinese food.

This place looked like a tiny stripclub. It was dark and only had red lights on so it was difficult to see the food you were served and it's quality. I ordered the Mapo Tofu because it's reviews were good. It was like old ground pork swimming in oil! It's literally soup made of just oil. There's a few cubes of tofu and they put a handful of chili peppers in it. I told the server couldn't eat it, so I paid for this overpriced garbage and left. Horrible.

This ain’t your ordinary Chinese-inspired joint. You’ll first learn of this when you walk in and see the giant dragon sprawled across the ceiling over the entire length of the restaurant, or the cut-out of Michael Jordan in the back corner across from the kitchen. 

To navigate to Mission Chinese, look for the sign under Lung Shan Restaurant. If you make it that far, you’re in for some tasty bites. I especially recommend the Thrice Cooked Bacon and Rice Cakes - it’s savory, it’s got a little kick and the rice cakes are just pillows of chewy deliciousness that ties it all together. 

When in SF, this should be a stop.
The food and decor here are great. The staff is very courteous and helpful. Would love to visit again. Recommend the fiery dumplings.
Great Chinese fusion. The sour chilli chicken was delicious and the macha noodles were pretty good too. The service is okay, but at least it's fast.

reviews.text: This is, hands down, my favorite bar. Dinner here is truly magical but it's the bar and the world class people behind it that secure its place in my heart. Megan created my girlfriend's favorite drink on her birthday. It helped inspire The Lost Garden Found which settled in on the menu for six months. Franco designed mine, a kind of Black Manhattan that contributed to the Don't Call Me Shirley which is on there right now. It's not that we're so great at choosing soon to be popular drinks, it's the aforementioned staff. Megan had a drink in USA Today and can design masterpieces based on just a few key questions. Franco is simply wonderful and makes me feel at home whether it's with clients or on date night. Thank you team Michael Mina.

I took my wife there recently for out anniversary. This place is fantastic but unfortunately it's still not Aqua. The lobster pot pie was very good and the staff was very nice, but with $21 martinis you would expect more. Deducting one star due to price.

My favorite here was not any of the entrees or desserts but rather the bread with the ricotta and honey spread. The bread was so soft and buttery and the spread was melt in your mouth delicious! The bread and spread was the best I have had anywhere!

We started off with the a half dozen oysters and the suckling pig. The oysters tasted fresh and the suckling pig had a nice crispy skin and was quite good in taste. For the entrees, we had the duck breast and the black cod. Both were really delicious. The duck skin was crispy and the meat was cooked perfectly. Presentation of all the foods were neat and artistic. Overall the food and experience were good. 

This is a nice fine dining experience to have in SF.
Went here for Valentine's day dinner last night. Service and food were amazing. I'm not sure the price point is correct. Good one time experience though.
Good but the waiter forgot my entry and never came to ask if everything was right. This place is very expensive so my expectations were high. Nice to go once but won't go back.

reviews.text: One of my favorite nightclubs to catch a good 🥁 & Bass show. Friendly staff and reasonable drink prices for SF
Excellent music, friendly staff, great dance vibe

I swore I wouldn't work in a venue when I moved here because I didn't want to loose the magic and love I have for sf's music scene... f8 has always been a favorite, so when they asked me if to lend a hand, of course I made the exception. Glad I did because I get to work with some of the most amazing insightful musicians and booking agents in the game, and I feel like I can make a real difference in making the dance community safe and accessible, the way it should b for  everyone. I feel very blessed to devote myself to this place. Forever a proud patron first, from icon to f8, this place is my cozy little home of low light and big big sound.

One of my favorite clubs in the city. Stamina Sundays always has free drum & bass shows, and they bring in great artists! The bartenders here are amazing and the people that come to the shows are always fun and friendly. See you on the dancefloor!

Spent two consecutive nights partying at this venue and I would definitely come back again the next SF trip. This place is ran like a dive bar, with a side catering to DJ shows. Not to mention they have very reasonable prices for drinks! If you sneak up to the back side of the venue, they even have a private artist lounge area that's open on certain occasions.  Great place when supporting a friend that's DJ'in or just a group of friends that are looking for a club night without the actual club experience.

reviews.text:
Bisou used to be a beautiful, nice French dining experience. Perfect for dates. We went for Sunday brunch recently. Our ears bled from the aggressively loud DJ. The music is good but would be too loud at half the volume. Conversation was not possible.  Even the waiter could not hear us. They got our order wrong. Then our food arrived cold. And incomplete. We asked for corrections but they didn’t arrive until after we were finished. 

Sadly it’s now devolved into a pretty trashy basic scene. Maybe it’s the bottomless mimosas. People come for the cheap day drunk. If that’s your crowd.

I've visited twice. First time, four stars. Would've been five, but one of the dishes was a miss (I had the foie gras tasting menu). Was nice and quiet and excellent service.
Second time, three stars...was cut in line (by someone who was with no one and had no one else in his party), and the host served that person ahead of me. Very rude, on both parts. Additionally, they only have one single occupancy bathroom operating for Sunday brunch, and it isn't kept the cleanest. The server was still excellent and the food was fine.

Cute spot with bottomless mimosa option for only $15. They also have a wide selection of different benedict breakfasts which almost everyone at my table got: crab cake, scallop, and duck leg. The scallop was my favorite, the scallops were perfectly cooked. I prefer a more lemony hollandaise, but it was still delicious. They also provide you with more than enough mimosas, they definitely do not skimp.

Chef Nick has been apart of my culinary adventures since I migrated here 6 years ago. Delicious and well thought out menu with a wide selection of wine and liquor. I always have a fabulous time when I grace Bisou Bistronomy with my presence.

Small French restaurant with a lovely decor. Perfect location on Market Street, next to Castro. Friendly and welcoming staff. The food is delicious, especially the seared scallops. Good wine list too.

reviews.text: Here for the buffet and views - and it did not disappoint. The food was satisfying and filling and they don’t skimp on the fancier fares, such as caviar. The views are just breathtaking, even at the reception, where we waited a bit because we arrived early. We were generously offered drinks while waiting. The walls have some cool vintage pictures that capture the vibe of the place in its early years.

Christmas Dinner Buffet was  $145/pp and not a turkey drumstick nor pumpkin pie to be seen. VERY disappointed that they did not actually offer ANY "standard Christmas fare" (even though it was advertised it would available). 
There were indeed many delicious-looking dishes to try, however, many fell short for me.  For example, the "braised short ribs were mostly fat, the lobster bisque soup (that I had craved all week after seeing it on the nenu) had ONE small piece of lobster in it (and I had to fish around and strain to get that!); and the lobster ravioli was so chewy and cold I left it on my plate. 

The dessert table almost made me laugh. Although it was colorful, The Mark was missed once again since there wasn't a single "typical" holiday dessert to be seen. One huge positive mention is that the bread pudding was outstanding! 

Maybe we will try the Christmas Brunch next year...
Get here early to grab the best views possible. Amazing history behind this landmark, spend some time reading the various stories behind the hotel and it’s penthouse lounge.

Jeez, as for martinis, you really can't ask for a nicer place to drink and unwind. The "100 Martini Menu" will keep your curiosity going throughout the night. The views are out of this world, too!
From casual polo shirts and khakis, to a "I'm about to get married and need to get stewed" tux, you'll fit in just fine.
George and the staff was amazing!!! Michael our waiter was impeccable.  Thank you for taking good care of us today.  Same incredible place when I was younger.... I love it...

reviews.text:
Hands down the best calamari that I have ever eaten.
