result.name: Schroeder's

reviews.text:
I've been here a few times and am certainly returning. Be warned however, Schroeder's doesn't exactly make for light eating.

Be it pretzel, burger, sauerkraut, or schnitzel-if it's from Schroeder's it's delicious. The staff is polite and surprisingly attentive considering this establishment, which is massive by SF standards, is usually packed to near capacity durring dinner/Happy hours. 

And now to the beer. If you are a beer person I can almost guarantee they will hace something for you. Also it's nice to find a place that will give a beer lover what they really want at dinner, plenty of beer at a reasonable price! Reasonable for what you are getting, not cheap keep in mind.

The environment is great if you are looking for a social setting, a quiet evening out not so much. I'd recommend reserving a table of you have a party however. Small groups will probably be able to squeeze in somewhere.

In short the worst thing about Schroeder's is the fact you may not get a seat there!

Bavaria made a baby in SF and Schroeder's was born. This place was remolded a few years ago giving it a true Bierzelt feeling. Go here for happy hour! They have specials on drinks and food. Great for big groups. Looking for Das Boot experience? They've got you covered, but be prepared to put a deposit down on the beer glass boot before they'll serve it up. The sausage and pretzel are delicious and perfect to absorb all your booze. They also, have a full bar for non-beer drinkers.
Great place for German food and beverages! I have had the pretzel and the sausages plate and recommend both, specially if you are hungry as the portions are big!

Old school German beer hall with a recently-renovated vibe. Not as hole-in-the-wall as it used to be (no more brautwurst buffet) and the prices reflect the 'upgrade'. Popular with the office crowd, packed during the after-work hours.

I've never been disappointed here. Of course, you have to like German food! Schroeder's has a decent number of choices, and everything I've tried has left me satisfied. Plus, they have a great beer selection.

reviews.text: Excellent little cafe near many attractions. Just a couple of blocks from many sights and shops, it's a perfect breakfast and lunch spot to get your day started or for a mid day break for a bite to refuel. I wish I had gotten some photos of our food, because it was truly fantastic looking and tasted great. More impressive when considering how quickly they were able to prepare and plate. Excellent portions, especially for the price. It is a very busy cafe, so if you don't mind the noise of the city, I would sit outside. We didn't have to wait for an outside table, but it would have been a few minutes for a table inside. The service was on point. Fast and friendly service and they had one staff member just freshening up coffees. Even brought brand new cups full of coffee and took the old ones when a fresh pot finished it's brew. I can't say enough about Hollywood Cafe. They are top notch. I look forward to eating hear again the next time I'm in San Francisco.

If you've woken up hungry this is the place to go. I was there last week. Despite the bad weather we still had to add our name to the wait list before we could get a table. It was so busy even though it was 8 am! We ordered a fruit salad, pancakes, coffee, tea and chocolate. Great service, overwhelmingly big breakfast, cheap prices. Be sure to plan in some waiting time if you think you might be in a hurry.
One of my favorite breakfast places in the city. Line can get long but the wait is worth it. Food is awesome and service is always wonderful.

Tried this place while on vacation and ended up going back 2 more times for breakfast. Food is fresh and of the best quality ive had at any breakfast place. Staff is very friendly and attentive. I don't see how you couldn't be happy. Great place.

Insanely amazing breakfast. I cannot brag about this place enough. Fantastic, friendly service. The Salmon & Shrimp Eggs Benedict has some quality ingredients that you wouldn’t normally find. And their fruit bowl also has some very unconventional (albeit amazing) fruit... to go along with the typical fruit there is kiwi, blackberries, raspberries, grapefruit, I mean, really good watermelon in December. Yes, I just typed that much for a fruit bowl!

Good food but not consummate with the prices. You would imagine they would now how to season food to get more flavor. It wasn't bland but not full of flavor from the deglazing they do for the sauce served with the steak. Dreadful coffee and not a non diary options for creamer. The service was average. The worst part was the patrons, which is no fault of the establishment.
One of the very best steak houses in S.F. Ambiance is very fun and eclectic. Staff is always friendly. Never have had a bad meal at Bobo's!

Never had a Bone in Filet before. Nice crust and a perfect medium rare. Melted in your mouth. Bobo's a steak propro!! Looking forward to coming here again.👍👍

Staff and service was great!  Look forward to my next visit.

reviews.text: It is deli, but maybe not quite Deli.  How I wish it really satisfied the craving.  Today, pastrami was at least half inedible fat. I tried it a couple years ago at their museum location, which was so bad I couldn't go back.  Time heals all wounds, so I tried again.  Grr. Next time maybe try corned beef.  Rye is a bit soft like white, but has good flavor.  Mustard is weak.  Pickles are pretty good.

Came here for the first time on Christmas. I’ll be back often. Showed up around 1:30. Right after I stepped in, they closed the doors to wrap up so the staff could get home for the holidays at a reasonable time (classy move). After ordering, they wished me a merry Christmas, and comped my meal! I was totally shocked. 

Food was fantastic. LEO scramble, super soft eggs and the most lox I’ve ever had in one (guess NYC is stingy). A dilly, salty mug of chicken broth - what a great idea btw - washed it down perfectly. Fun game: put your broth mug next to your coffee mug and reach for one at random when you’re thirsty. You’ll be happy either way. 

Oh they also let a woman, who ordered carry-out with no where to take it, eat inside instead, then encouraged us two solo diners to talk to each other. We had a great conversation. 

They sent us home with apricot rugelach. Sweet and tart in all the right ways. 

Can’t guarantee you’ll have the same experience but it’s clear these folks have food AND service nailed down so you will definitely leave happy.
Don't worry too much about the lines... a lot of people are buying to take away so you still may be able to find seats

We spent 30 mins making our way through SF'S lovely traffic to taste the most expensively priced smoked salmon, 1 lb for 40 bucks, if I did not have to worry about money it's a great place to buy from.
The people there are modernly old fashion.
Sorry for no pictures, still can taste the experience.
My favorite breakfast spot in SF! The line is never that long, moves quickly and always able to grab a seat by the time my food is out. Consistently deliciously comforting.

reviews.text: I went with a colleague for dinner. Had the Mac and cheese to start which was AMAZING! Probably top 5 I've ever had before. It was truly that delicious. Crumbled bacon on top and perfect, creamy cheese all over. It was something special. I also had the fried chicken which was tasty and crispy. Fairly priced although the wines are a little on the pricey side. Definitely gets packed so make a reservation.

Great drinks and the fried chicken was good. I liked the cornbread that came with the table.  Burger was delicious.  Definitely great comfort food and would love to try more here. It was really busy even at 9pm.  We had no reservations but they were able to seat us.

Nipped here after a quick search. No expectations but well, what a great place.  Tuesday night 8pm and the place was almost full.  Being a solo diner I say at the bar.  The have my favourite gin, Monkey 47, so that's always a good start. The barkeeper suggested a gin old fashioned with the 47 - what a superb drink.  I had the pork chop.  I really enjoyed it.  The food service was quick. $55 for drink and chop - not too bad.  Somewhere I will visit again.

This place was really great. Everything I look for in a good date night out. The restaurant is tucked in a narrow road, which reminds me of all the little roads in European cities. Service was excellent and the food was really tasty. The drink menu also had some great options, including the classics, which I love. As for the food, I really enjoyed my meal. The menu isn't huge but has a variety of items which would make this a great place even for a pickier eater. I can't wait to come back.

AMAZING! From the service to the food and drinks, this place will definitely be my go to restaurant when I visit the city! The staff was extremely accommodating to my party of 12. We had an absolute fantastic time! Thank you Hops and Hominy for making my husband's birthday one to remember!!!

reviews.text: We have been coming here for the last 3 or 4 years and it has been consistently good.  Survive , food and atmosphere.  Prices have gone up all over SF so you are paying more but I have paid more at other restaurants and enjoyed it less.  We recommend it for their consistency.

Wanted to go for lunch but just missed the cutoff (2:30pm) Ended up with bar menu... Meatballs were very salty... doesnt seem to be all beef (mixed with sausage?). But spaghetti & meatball was one of the better items. For the price I expect better quality and better service. Not sure if it was bc it's from the bar menu?

I recommend this place to my friends because I had great experiences in the past. They both wanted to eat something from the main dinner menu but all I wanted was the sausage pizza from the bar menu. I was informed that we were unable to have the pizza served at the main restaurant so we would all have to sit at the bar area. Now I do understand you don't want the bar menu being eaten in the restaurant but when it's only 1 out of 3 of us, I think you should be able to make an exception. However it was the way this situation was handled we were upset with. After being moved to the bar area they were so upset and embarrassed they decided to walk out and not order any food at all. As you can imagine this really upset me as I had recommended it to them in the first place. They didn't want to eat main food in the bar area and your restaurant didn't want me to eat a pizza in the restaurant so we were at a loss. The way I would of liked it to be dealt with would of been to make an exception that on this one occasion seen as the other two were willing to eat from the main menu. As it turned out you lost 3 customers that night and will have to fight to get me back in there which is sad as I usually enjoy it.
The orrichette is awesome and the gluten free pizza isvery good, too. The sun-dried tomato relish they serve with the bread is ever so light and delicious. We got a second helping of that!

I had the best breakfast I've had in a long time. If not ever. I ordered the crab cake Benedict and my boyfriend got the waffle. The Mimosa was quite delicious and well. The waiter was a bit odd, and my drink took a while, but otherwise I would recommend breakfast here.
